1
00:00:32,912 --> 00:00:36,382
(The final check before rehearsal)

2
00:00:36,752 --> 00:00:37,952
It suits you.

3
00:00:38,192 --> 00:00:39,192
(The costumes...)

4
00:00:39,193 --> 00:00:42,022
(are ready.)

5
00:00:42,594 --> 00:00:43,632
(The music...)

6
00:00:43,862 --> 00:00:44,862
(is ready.)

7
00:00:44,862 --> 00:00:45,862
(Roaring)

8
00:00:45,863 --> 00:00:47,001
(The music is ready.)

9
00:00:47,002 --> 00:00:48,002
Louder!

10
00:00:48,003 --> 00:00:49,361
(Good...)

11
00:00:49,362 --> 00:00:50,372
(vocalization!)

12
00:00:50,732 --> 00:00:52,132
(What? The Wicked Witch of the West?)

13
00:00:52,543 --> 00:00:54,313
(Recharged fully with acting skills)

14
00:00:55,583 --> 00:00:58,183
(Off to the stage rehearsal)

15
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:02,123
(Even Mr. CO is here.)

16
00:01:03,253 --> 00:01:05,092
(The moment the imaginary stage...)

17
00:01:05,093 --> 00:01:07,563
(became reality!)

18
00:01:08,763 --> 00:01:10,563
(But...)

19
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:15,672
(the wild wind...)

20
00:01:15,673 --> 00:01:18,702
(and worrisome unexpected events)

21
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:20,543
- It seems to be impossible.
- It's so chaotic, right?

22
00:01:20,613 --> 00:01:22,243
(Backstage is chaotic.)

23
00:01:23,373 --> 00:01:26,443
(The kids' rehearsal begins now.)

24
00:01:27,183 --> 00:01:29,112
- Today is...
- Rehearsal day.

25
00:01:29,113 --> 00:01:33,253
(Today is rehearsal day!)

26
00:01:33,453 --> 00:01:34,852
Kids, could you go up on stage?

27
00:01:34,853 --> 00:01:36,592
(The kids stand on stage for the first time.)

28
00:01:36,593 --> 00:01:38,263
They're already acting on stage.

29
00:01:38,763 --> 00:01:40,593
The stage looks bigger with the kids on it.

30
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,962
(Touched)

31
00:01:42,963 --> 00:01:45,232
- Kids.
- Is this how parents feel?

32
00:01:45,233 --> 00:01:46,533
Now then...

33
00:01:47,173 --> 00:01:49,133
- We're going to do a run-through.
- Okay.

34
00:01:49,173 --> 00:01:51,272
There will be music and all. Got it?

35
00:01:51,273 --> 00:01:52,743
- Yes.
- Good.

36
00:01:54,213 --> 00:01:56,112
(Parent KUN has come to the backstage.)

37
00:01:56,113 --> 00:01:57,483
- Here's your fur.
- Cool.

38
00:01:58,143 --> 00:01:59,183
I can help you.

39
00:01:59,543 --> 00:02:01,052
- Mr. CO.
- Yes?

40
00:02:01,053 --> 00:02:02,782
You promised to come every two days,

41
00:02:02,783 --> 00:02:03,783
but I got upset because you didn't come...

42
00:02:03,783 --> 00:02:04,783
when it had been four days.

43
00:02:04,784 --> 00:02:05,852
I'm sorry.

44
00:02:05,853 --> 00:02:07,653
I was making music.

45
00:02:07,953 --> 00:02:10,662
But I didn't have what it took to make them.

46
00:02:10,663 --> 00:02:12,162
So putting in more effort took a bit more time.

47
00:02:12,163 --> 00:02:13,933
Won Jin's fur is getting everywhere.

48
00:02:14,563 --> 00:02:16,332
- This one...
- If you see...

49
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,902
- Mr. CO.
- Yes?

50
00:02:17,903 --> 00:02:21,272
My lion fur to your friends in...

51
00:02:21,273 --> 00:02:22,903
- "Running Man." - Should I give it to them?

52
00:02:23,473 --> 00:02:26,542
I'll put this between my phone and my phone case.

53
00:02:26,543 --> 00:02:27,873
- Okay?
- Okay.

54
00:02:29,173 --> 00:02:32,412
- It's too windy, like it's winter.
- Tell others that the students...

55
00:02:32,413 --> 00:02:34,182
- Okay.
- of the acting class...

56
00:02:34,183 --> 00:02:35,712
gave you the lion fur.

57
00:02:35,713 --> 00:02:37,052
That it's from you and your friends?

58
00:02:37,053 --> 00:02:38,953
I'll put it in the back of my phone case right now.

59
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:40,392
Give me a high five.

60
00:02:40,393 --> 00:02:41,893
Please remember me.

61
00:02:43,253 --> 00:02:46,262
Hyo Min, start acting once you hear the sound of the crows.

62
00:02:46,263 --> 00:02:48,663
That's when the curtains will open, and you'll see the audience. Okay?

63
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:51,163
Everyone is ready, right?

64
00:02:51,563 --> 00:02:52,862
Yes, we are.

65
00:02:52,863 --> 00:02:55,432
Good. The actors and actresses are in place, yes?

66
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:57,103
Kids, we're about to start.

67
00:02:58,803 --> 00:03:01,173
Here we go. Okay.

68
00:03:02,643 --> 00:03:04,482
Okay. Let's do this.

69
00:03:04,483 --> 00:03:05,882
(The stage rehearsal begins.)

70
00:03:05,883 --> 00:03:06,913
Let's get going.

71
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:11,223
Here we go. Ready, and get on stage.

72
00:03:13,923 --> 00:03:17,693
(The narrator goes up on stage.)

73
00:03:18,623 --> 00:03:21,163
Because of the whirlwind,

74
00:03:21,263 --> 00:03:24,233
Dorothy and her house, which was in Mungyeong,

75
00:03:24,463 --> 00:03:27,433
were blown to the strange yet mystical world of Oz.

76
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,402
The curtains open.

77
00:03:29,403 --> 00:03:32,943
(Number 1, Dorothy's scene)

78
00:03:36,373 --> 00:03:38,613
Once I close the door, open it again when you enter!

79
00:03:39,983 --> 00:03:41,053
Go.

80
00:03:41,783 --> 00:03:45,623
(Dorothy opens the door and appears with the sound of the door opening.)

81
00:03:46,323 --> 00:03:48,993
(Appearing at the perfect time)

82
00:03:51,123 --> 00:03:53,893
(Where am I?)

83
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:59,663
(Toto appears after Dorothy.)

84
00:04:00,473 --> 00:04:03,773
(Following behind, Toto looks around in amazement.)

85
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:08,473
My gosh, we're not in Mungyeong!

86
00:04:08,813 --> 00:04:11,283
Enchanting! It's all colorful!

87
00:04:11,913 --> 00:04:13,483
How dazzling!

88
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:14,852
How dazzling!

89
00:04:14,853 --> 00:04:16,653
Sniff, the scent of flowers!

90
00:04:16,783 --> 00:04:18,383
Sniff, the scent of flowers!

91
00:04:19,453 --> 00:04:21,993
- I can talk!
- Toto can talk!

92
00:04:23,593 --> 00:04:25,693
(As expected!)

93
00:04:26,593 --> 00:04:28,362
And Ju Eun, come over here.

94
00:04:28,363 --> 00:04:31,602
Walk around the back and go to the right, okay?

95
00:04:31,603 --> 00:04:32,903
- Okay.
- Go.

96
00:04:34,603 --> 00:04:37,643
(Ju Eun is brave even on stage.)

97
00:04:38,373 --> 00:04:40,342
Let's set out together!

98
00:04:40,343 --> 00:04:41,413
- Hooray!
- Hooray!

99
00:04:42,643 --> 00:04:44,183
In 1, 2, 3.

100
00:04:44,943 --> 00:04:47,652
Okay. You leave after "in 1, 2, 3," okay?

101
00:04:47,653 --> 00:04:49,213
Please exit joyfully.

102
00:04:50,323 --> 00:04:54,253
(Leaving while jumping to the music made by Mr. CO)

103
00:04:56,053 --> 00:04:58,263
(After the curtains close)

104
00:04:58,393 --> 00:05:01,463
Hyo Min, go once the curtains are fully closed.

105
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:05,633
(Here goes Potato.)

106
00:05:05,634 --> 00:05:07,103
The shoes.

107
00:05:08,103 --> 00:05:10,942
The paper door, arrow, out.

108
00:05:10,943 --> 00:05:11,943
(Setting up the scarecrow set quickly...)

109
00:05:11,943 --> 00:05:12,943
(while curtains are closed.)

110
00:05:13,843 --> 00:05:14,943
Scarecrow.

111
00:05:15,113 --> 00:05:17,212
Stand with your arms apart.

112
00:05:17,213 --> 00:05:18,913
Around there. That's it.

113
00:05:20,283 --> 00:05:22,582
Is Hyo Min in position?

114
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:24,152
(Through the intercom)

115
00:05:24,153 --> 00:05:25,353
Is Hyo Min in position?

116
00:05:26,023 --> 00:05:28,293
- The music has to keep playing.
- Okay.

117
00:05:29,493 --> 00:05:31,992
And... Is Hyo Min in position?

118
00:05:31,993 --> 00:05:33,223
(Asking in desperation)

119
00:05:33,893 --> 00:05:36,363
(Didn't hear her as he's not wearing the intercom)

120
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:39,803
Hyo Min, talk loudly. Okay?

121
00:05:41,573 --> 00:05:44,443
Teachers, please tell me if Hyo Min is in position.

122
00:05:45,203 --> 00:05:46,903
Yes, right now...

123
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:51,813
Okay. Go ahead, Ms. Kim.

124
00:05:52,343 --> 00:05:53,383
You can start now.

125
00:05:54,153 --> 00:05:56,512
Here's the sound of the crows.

126
00:05:56,513 --> 00:05:57,683
(The sound of the crows plays)

127
00:05:58,723 --> 00:05:59,882
The curtains open.

128
00:05:59,883 --> 00:06:04,192
(Number 2, the Scarecrow's scene)

129
00:06:04,193 --> 00:06:05,793
Your lines, Hyo Min.

130
00:06:06,323 --> 00:06:08,932
These crows! They're not scared of me anymore.

131
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,302
- Go.
- Good job.

132
00:06:11,303 --> 00:06:12,363
(Dorothy and Toto enter.)

133
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,232
- Hi.
- Hi.

134
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:17,802
What nice weather. Thanks for greeting me...

135
00:06:17,803 --> 00:06:19,173
when even the crows look down on me.

136
00:06:19,403 --> 00:06:21,242
Can't you get down from there?

137
00:06:21,243 --> 00:06:24,513
No, I can't do it alone because of the pole on my back.

138
00:06:25,113 --> 00:06:26,943
We'll help you down!

139
00:06:27,283 --> 00:06:28,582
- Down you go!
- Down you go!

140
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:30,683
(Going down)

141
00:06:31,553 --> 00:06:33,923
(He's good!)

142
00:06:34,253 --> 00:06:37,493
Why don't we all set out together?

143
00:06:37,663 --> 00:06:38,723
- Hooray!
- Hooray!

144
00:06:40,793 --> 00:06:43,432
(After two big laps, Dorothy, Toto, and the Scarecrow set out together.)

145
00:06:43,433 --> 00:06:44,503
One more lap.

146
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:51,173
(Number 3, the Tin Man's scene)

147
00:06:52,273 --> 00:06:55,543
Dorothy, Toto should be taking the lead in this scene.

148
00:06:55,843 --> 00:06:57,383
(Got it!)

149
00:06:57,983 --> 00:07:00,553
- It hurts.
- Sniff.

150
00:07:00,683 --> 00:07:03,213
Sniff, I found something!

151
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:06,883
Hi. Do you mind helping me out a bit?

152
00:07:07,353 --> 00:07:08,823
No, how may I help you?

153
00:07:09,093 --> 00:07:11,292
There's an oil can around my waist.

154
00:07:11,293 --> 00:07:12,422
Give me a bit of oiling.

155
00:07:12,423 --> 00:07:14,593
(Tin Man: With more confidence)

156
00:07:15,863 --> 00:07:19,663
(Dorothy oils the Tin Man.)

157
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:22,872
Can Dorothy make sound effects of spraying the oil?

158
00:07:22,873 --> 00:07:24,443
- Spritz.
- "Spritz!"

159
00:07:24,673 --> 00:07:25,803
Nice.

160
00:07:26,573 --> 00:07:27,672
- Spritz.
- Spritz!

161
00:07:27,673 --> 00:07:30,512
(Makes the sound effect cutely)

162
00:07:30,513 --> 00:07:31,513
Okay.

163
00:07:31,514 --> 00:07:34,313
You should also visit the Wizard of Oz and make a wish.

164
00:07:34,613 --> 00:07:36,712
I'll ask him for a heart.

165
00:07:36,713 --> 00:07:39,583
I want a heart filled with kindness.

166
00:07:40,023 --> 00:07:42,052
I'd like to ask for a brain.

167
00:07:42,053 --> 00:07:44,192
If I have a heart but no brain...

168
00:07:44,193 --> 00:07:46,662
(Saying the lines without a hitch)

169
00:07:46,663 --> 00:07:49,033
- I wouldn't know what to do.
- My gosh.

170
00:07:51,103 --> 00:07:52,832
- Hey...
- What? He's good.

171
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:55,102
- can't you chop the trees for us?
- He was born to perform.

172
00:07:55,103 --> 00:07:58,072
I may not have a heart, but I surely can chop the trees.

173
00:07:58,073 --> 00:07:59,273
That's it. Right there.

174
00:07:59,773 --> 00:08:00,812
Chop!

175
00:08:00,813 --> 00:08:02,112
(The others are happy as the Tin Man makes a path.)

176
00:08:02,113 --> 00:08:03,143
Yes.

177
00:08:04,313 --> 00:08:05,813
- That's it.
- Chop!

178
00:08:06,343 --> 00:08:07,753
Nice.

179
00:08:07,853 --> 00:08:10,583
- Yes!
- Nice!

180
00:08:11,323 --> 00:08:12,582
Exit.

181
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,292
(High five!)

182
00:08:14,293 --> 00:08:17,323
Well done.

183
00:08:18,393 --> 00:08:20,093
Amazing!

184
00:08:21,263 --> 00:08:22,792
Next is the Lion.

185
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:24,403
Wait here. Hold on.

186
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:26,732
- I'll cue you to appear.
- Here's the music.

187
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:27,873
Not yet.

188
00:08:28,933 --> 00:08:30,703
Music, cue.

189
00:08:31,573 --> 00:08:33,373
Once music starts, go on the stage.

190
00:08:33,603 --> 00:08:35,043
Roar loudly, okay?

191
00:08:35,873 --> 00:08:40,243
(A spooky mood, everyone appears nervously.)

192
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:44,683
(Barking)

193
00:08:45,453 --> 00:08:49,053
(Barking)

194
00:08:52,423 --> 00:08:53,423
(Roaring)

195
00:08:53,424 --> 00:08:54,492
(Whimpering)

196
00:08:54,493 --> 00:08:55,533
Toto!

197
00:08:55,963 --> 00:08:57,703
(Dorothy punches.)

198
00:08:58,763 --> 00:09:01,872
(The great actors and actresses make no mistakes.)

199
00:09:01,873 --> 00:09:03,773
Ju Eun, get ready.

200
00:09:05,073 --> 00:09:06,702
Take me with you.

201
00:09:06,703 --> 00:09:09,113
(Where are you going?)

202
00:09:10,273 --> 00:09:11,343
Here.

203
00:09:11,883 --> 00:09:13,082
"Let's go meet him."

204
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:15,913
(Ready to go in lightning speed)

205
00:09:16,483 --> 00:09:18,152
The curtains are closing.

206
00:09:18,153 --> 00:09:20,282
(After the scene of the lion's appearance)

207
00:09:20,283 --> 00:09:22,492
While the curtains close, get into position.

208
00:09:22,493 --> 00:09:23,522
Okay.

209
00:09:23,523 --> 00:09:26,162
(Narrator Ju Eun's turn)

210
00:09:26,163 --> 00:09:27,863
The journey was peaceful.

211
00:09:28,263 --> 00:09:29,263
Okay.

212
00:09:29,593 --> 00:09:30,833
Yes, leave the stage.

213
00:09:31,203 --> 00:09:32,962
Don't we have to go to that side?

214
00:09:32,963 --> 00:09:34,232
Get in line again.

215
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:35,902
The journey was peaceful.

216
00:09:35,903 --> 00:09:37,542
Get in line again.

217
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:38,902
You're here.

218
00:09:38,903 --> 00:09:41,142
Get in line like we practiced, okay?

219
00:09:41,143 --> 00:09:42,143
- Okay.
- Good.

220
00:09:42,643 --> 00:09:44,413
I forgot one of my lines.

221
00:09:44,843 --> 00:09:46,013
Stand in front of me.

222
00:09:46,783 --> 00:09:49,812
However, the peaceful journey didn't last long.

223
00:09:49,813 --> 00:09:50,823
(Number 5, the Witch's kidnapping scene)

224
00:09:52,683 --> 00:09:55,893
(Playing the Witch song)

225
00:09:58,693 --> 00:10:01,933
(Looking around)

226
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,333
(Toto)

227
00:10:04,334 --> 00:10:06,962
I smell fire.

228
00:10:06,963 --> 00:10:10,173
Fire? No! My straws will all burn!

229
00:10:11,703 --> 00:10:13,773
(The Witch has appeared.)

230
00:10:15,343 --> 00:10:16,973
(Screaming)

231
00:10:17,213 --> 00:10:19,983
Killing your younger sister was a coincidence!

232
00:10:20,243 --> 00:10:23,213
The whirlwind dropped my house on her!

233
00:10:24,283 --> 00:10:26,053
That doesn't matter!

234
00:10:26,223 --> 00:10:28,623
What I want is your silver shoes!

235
00:10:29,553 --> 00:10:32,323
What? But these silver shoes are just a pair of shoes.

236
00:10:33,893 --> 00:10:37,093
(Eat this!)

237
00:10:38,063 --> 00:10:39,262
Dorothy!

238
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:41,473
(Dorothy gets kidnapped by the Witch.)

239
00:10:42,703 --> 00:10:46,403
(The curtain closes.)

240
00:10:47,843 --> 00:10:48,843
(It's time for the lake set.)

241
00:10:48,844 --> 00:10:50,742
- Dorothy, say your lines...
- Here.

242
00:10:50,743 --> 00:10:52,883
- while the curtains are closing.
- This is the lake, okay?

243
00:10:53,543 --> 00:10:55,682
Listen. This is important.

244
00:10:55,683 --> 00:10:56,952
There are two lakes here.

245
00:10:56,953 --> 00:10:58,482
Got it. I should go in between, right?

246
00:10:58,483 --> 00:10:59,853
Yes, in between.

247
00:11:00,583 --> 00:11:02,492
Go in between the two, okay?

248
00:11:02,493 --> 00:11:03,952
(She must go in between.)

249
00:11:03,953 --> 00:11:05,293
Can we open the curtains?

250
00:11:05,563 --> 00:11:07,323
Give us a second.

251
00:11:07,893 --> 00:11:10,293
Five, four, three,

252
00:11:10,763 --> 00:11:12,602
two, action. Open them.

253
00:11:12,603 --> 00:11:13,663
The curtains open.

254
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:19,403
(Dorothy's friends have come to rescue Dorothy.)

255
00:11:22,143 --> 00:11:23,143
Dorothy.

256
00:11:23,144 --> 00:11:25,543
Dorothy's across the lake.

257
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:28,512
How can we get rid of the Witch and rescue Dorothy?

258
00:11:28,513 --> 00:11:30,083
Let's rescue her!

259
00:11:33,783 --> 00:11:37,153
(Great teamwork)

260
00:11:38,123 --> 00:11:39,793
- Good.
- Nice.

261
00:11:40,093 --> 00:11:41,133
Good.

262
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:43,892
I'll become the bridge.

263
00:11:43,893 --> 00:11:46,303
My tin pieces will work as a sturdy bridge.

264
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:48,733
Go defeat the Witch and rescue Dorothy.

265
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,172
We can't do that. The moment your body touches water,

266
00:11:51,173 --> 00:11:53,403
you'll rust and become all stiff.

267
00:11:53,843 --> 00:11:55,642
Even if my body becomes all stiff,

268
00:11:55,643 --> 00:11:57,583
I want to rescue Dorothy.

269
00:11:58,013 --> 00:11:59,883
Guys!

270
00:12:00,213 --> 00:12:02,683
I'll cross the lake.

271
00:12:02,953 --> 00:12:05,723
With my strong legs,

272
00:12:05,983 --> 00:12:07,722
I'll rescue Dorothy.

273
00:12:07,723 --> 00:12:08,993
His shoes are adorable.

274
00:12:09,253 --> 00:12:11,662
Jump in 1, 2, 3.

275
00:12:11,663 --> 00:12:12,963
(Here goes the Lion!)

276
00:12:15,193 --> 00:12:17,333
(Jumped with his strong legs)

277
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:21,133
How did you figure out my weakness!

278
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,573
Water is deadly!

279
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:26,303
I've still got so many wicked things to do!

280
00:12:26,573 --> 00:12:28,243
What a bummer. Goodbye!

281
00:12:28,813 --> 00:12:29,813
(Going down)

282
00:12:29,814 --> 00:12:31,483
- Well done. Okay.
- Okay.

283
00:12:31,683 --> 00:12:33,283
In 1, 2, 3.

284
00:12:33,483 --> 00:12:36,212
- Hooray! The Lion did it!
- Hooray! The Lion did it!

285
00:12:36,213 --> 00:12:38,282
- Thank you, Lion!
- Okay.

286
00:12:38,283 --> 00:12:39,283
The chorus.

287
00:12:39,284 --> 00:12:42,452
The chorus will begin right where you are.

288
00:12:42,453 --> 00:12:44,522
Right there and not the center of the stage?

289
00:12:44,523 --> 00:12:45,823
- Yes.
- Okay.

290
00:12:46,323 --> 00:12:48,662
Kids, move a bit to the front of the stage.

291
00:12:48,663 --> 00:12:50,462
(Rearranging thanks to Mr. CO)

292
00:12:50,463 --> 00:12:52,632
Okay, right around there. Remember it, okay?

293
00:12:52,633 --> 00:12:53,633
- Okay.
- Okay.

294
00:12:53,634 --> 00:12:54,703
Okay.

295
00:12:54,973 --> 00:12:56,372
- The chorus?
- Start the chorus.

296
00:12:56,373 --> 00:12:58,442
(Number 6, the chorus scene)

297
00:12:58,443 --> 00:12:59,673
Loudly and cheerfully.

298
00:12:59,843 --> 00:13:03,573
(Cheerfully!)

299
00:13:05,313 --> 00:13:09,082
(With courage, the Lion lends a hand)

300
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:12,323
(The Scarecrow's wisdom is so grand)

301
00:13:13,383 --> 00:13:15,553
(Highly satisfied)

302
00:13:16,423 --> 00:13:19,493
(A performance in perfect sync)

303
00:13:20,593 --> 00:13:23,193
(The choreographer is deeply moved.)

304
00:13:23,863 --> 00:13:27,003
(Good!)

305
00:13:27,503 --> 00:13:30,403
(A good friend with a heart so wide)

306
00:13:31,203 --> 00:13:34,143
(With Dorothy by our side)

307
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:37,743
(It's already the climax.)

308
00:13:40,283 --> 00:13:41,512
(From the singing to the choreography,)

309
00:13:41,513 --> 00:13:42,752
(everything is perfect!)

310
00:13:42,753 --> 00:13:45,652
Okay, the curtains close.

311
00:13:45,653 --> 00:13:47,322
(Cheer!)

312
00:13:47,323 --> 00:13:49,052
The curtains should close faster.

313
00:13:49,053 --> 00:13:51,792
Please close them on "our side."

314
00:13:51,793 --> 00:13:53,323
(All that's left is the Wizard scene.)

315
00:13:53,593 --> 00:13:54,863
Let's take the lake out!

316
00:13:55,393 --> 00:13:57,633
Take the lake out!

317
00:13:58,303 --> 00:13:59,632
Run! Take it out!

318
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:02,103
- Okay, take the lake out.
- Take the lake out.

319
00:14:02,373 --> 00:14:04,442
Set up the castle gate at the same time.

320
00:14:04,443 --> 00:14:05,573
Here.

321
00:14:05,673 --> 00:14:06,673
(Startled)

322
00:14:06,674 --> 00:14:08,573
The Wizard's curtains are set up.

323
00:14:08,843 --> 00:14:11,282
- Ha Yun the Gatekeeper, get ready.
- Hold on.

324
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:12,343
I'll take it out.

325
00:14:12,943 --> 00:14:14,513
Why is it so heavy?

326
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:16,383
It's super heavy.

327
00:14:16,683 --> 00:14:18,023
(Shocked)

328
00:14:19,053 --> 00:14:20,723
(Laughing)

329
00:14:21,153 --> 00:14:23,122
Give me a minute.

330
00:14:23,123 --> 00:14:24,362
(The rush can be heard outside the stage.)

331
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:25,392
Let's go. Hurry.

332
00:14:25,393 --> 00:14:27,222
It's like a play within a play.

333
00:14:27,223 --> 00:14:28,662
(North Pole Teacher's 1-man play once the curtains close)

334
00:14:28,663 --> 00:14:31,162
A bit more.

335
00:14:31,163 --> 00:14:32,602
(The curtains to cover the Wizard are here.)

336
00:14:32,603 --> 00:14:35,002
Right here. Perfect.

337
00:14:35,003 --> 00:14:37,003
All set. Okay. Close the curtains.

338
00:14:37,573 --> 00:14:39,372
The Gatekeeper should be in front at first.

339
00:14:39,373 --> 00:14:40,573
Where's Ha Yun?

340
00:14:41,873 --> 00:14:43,012
Excuse me for a minute.

341
00:14:43,013 --> 00:14:44,742
(Ms. Kim stops the rehearsal and goes on stage.)

342
00:14:44,743 --> 00:14:46,812
- I'll put it here.
- Ms. Kim.

343
00:14:46,813 --> 00:14:48,882
(A big paper doll appears.)

344
00:14:48,883 --> 00:14:51,352
- What?
- Ha Yun, come here for a second.

345
00:14:51,353 --> 00:14:52,852
- Ha Yun!
- Ha Yun!

346
00:14:52,853 --> 00:14:54,793
- Ha Yun!
- Send him here.

347
00:14:55,923 --> 00:14:59,162
(The Wizard appears while hiding his identity.)

348
00:14:59,163 --> 00:15:01,533
I'm the Great Wizard of Oz.

349
00:15:01,863 --> 00:15:04,633
Defeat the Wicked Witch of the West, and I'll make your wish come true.

350
00:15:05,063 --> 00:15:06,262
Okay, you do it.

351
00:15:06,263 --> 00:15:08,802
Try moving it next to him.

352
00:15:08,803 --> 00:15:10,503
- I'll be doing it for you.
- Test out the lights.

353
00:15:11,503 --> 00:15:13,943
- Let's try it out.
- Okay. Let's start from here.

354
00:15:14,673 --> 00:15:16,512
- In front.
- Starting with the Gatekeeper.

355
00:15:16,513 --> 00:15:18,713
Everyone, we'll start with the Gatekeeper.

356
00:15:19,483 --> 00:15:21,512
Come here, in front of the curtains.

357
00:15:21,513 --> 00:15:23,813
(The Wizard's wand to the Gatekeeper?)

358
00:15:24,683 --> 00:15:27,852
Ha Yun shouldn't be wearing the Wizard's hat or holding the wand.

359
00:15:27,853 --> 00:15:28,952
Yes, he's not.

360
00:15:28,953 --> 00:15:31,062
The glasses are in your pocket, yes?

361
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:32,493
I don't have the glasses.

362
00:15:34,993 --> 00:15:36,233
The glasses.

363
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:38,233
- Okay.
- Hold on.

364
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:41,003
Here. About 15 seconds during the real play?

365
00:15:41,803 --> 00:15:43,502
- Yes, 15 seconds.
- About 15 seconds.

366
00:15:43,503 --> 00:15:45,073
- Let's see if it's possible.
- Okay.

367
00:15:45,673 --> 00:15:46,703
Okay.

368
00:15:48,073 --> 00:15:49,613
- Once you get here...
- Yes?

369
00:15:49,743 --> 00:15:52,912
Whenever you're on stage,

370
00:15:52,913 --> 00:15:54,382
- get the glasses first, okay?
- Okay.

371
00:15:54,383 --> 00:15:56,513
- You must have them with you.
- Okay.

372
00:15:57,013 --> 00:15:58,582
Promise me. I'll keep it in mind too.

373
00:15:58,583 --> 00:15:59,583
Okay.

374
00:16:00,653 --> 00:16:02,553
The curtains open.

375
00:16:03,753 --> 00:16:06,263
(The Gatekeeper appears in front of the castle gate.)

376
00:16:07,693 --> 00:16:08,892
(Singing)

377
00:16:08,893 --> 00:16:10,063
(Singing)

378
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:12,503
You can appear while laughing.

379
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:16,032
(Dorothy and her friends spot the Gatekeeper.)

380
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:17,903
A new scent! Hi!

381
00:16:18,303 --> 00:16:22,113
Hi, we're here to meet the Wizard of Oz.

382
00:16:22,473 --> 00:16:25,743
Before meeting the Wizard, you must put on these glasses.

383
00:16:25,843 --> 00:16:28,453
You must call him after putting them on.

384
00:16:29,283 --> 00:16:31,223
(Feeling proud)

385
00:16:32,753 --> 00:16:34,822
(The Gatekeeper gives each a pair of black glasses.)

386
00:16:34,823 --> 00:16:35,853
Okay.

387
00:16:36,153 --> 00:16:37,392
Ha Yun leaves.

388
00:16:37,393 --> 00:16:39,292
Ha Yun leaves after giving out the glasses.

389
00:16:39,293 --> 00:16:40,922
- Remember it, okay?
- Okay.

390
00:16:40,923 --> 00:16:42,832
(Transforming into the Wizard fast)

391
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,862
All set? Okay, good.

392
00:16:44,863 --> 00:16:47,202
Okay. Go to the back. Nice.

393
00:16:47,203 --> 00:16:49,632
(Heading to the back of the castle gate)

394
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,303
- Ha Yun is ready.
- Gosh, dear.

395
00:16:51,803 --> 00:16:54,813
- All set. He's all ready.
- Gosh, no.

396
00:16:55,143 --> 00:16:58,113
Everyone, hold hands together.

397
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:00,782
Where...Where are you?

398
00:17:00,783 --> 00:17:03,183
- Let's hold hands.
- The Scarecrow. Let's hold hands.

399
00:17:03,383 --> 00:17:04,582
Who are you?

400
00:17:04,583 --> 00:17:06,053
- It's you, Toto.
- Yes, it's me.

401
00:17:06,483 --> 00:17:08,153
Good.

402
00:17:08,323 --> 00:17:10,153
I can't see a thing.

403
00:17:10,253 --> 00:17:11,292
How are they so good?

404
00:17:11,293 --> 00:17:12,763
(Startled)

405
00:17:12,863 --> 00:17:15,392
- Wizard of Oz!
- Wizard of Oz!

406
00:17:15,393 --> 00:17:18,233
- Open the gate!
- Open the gate!

407
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:21,133
(The castle gate opens.)

408
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:25,403
(But the Wizard's shadow isn't there.)

409
00:17:26,803 --> 00:17:28,043
Gosh, lights.

410
00:17:29,013 --> 00:17:31,083
Potato Teacher? Where is he?

411
00:17:34,913 --> 00:17:35,913
My goodness, no.

412
00:17:40,053 --> 00:17:42,522
(Potato Teacher came running a bit late.)

413
00:17:42,523 --> 00:17:43,623
Potato Teacher... There he is.

414
00:17:45,723 --> 00:17:48,232
Potato Teacher, you need to stay ready.

415
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:49,233
(The shadow is late.)

416
00:17:50,293 --> 00:17:52,703
(Sorry.)

417
00:17:53,133 --> 00:17:56,372
I'm the great Wizard of Oz.

418
00:17:56,373 --> 00:17:59,243
Defeat the Wicked Witch of the West, and I shall grant your wish.

419
00:17:59,343 --> 00:18:00,473
The Wicked Witch?

420
00:18:00,573 --> 00:18:04,143
But we had already defeated her on our way here.

421
00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:07,342
Sniff, it smells the same as before!

422
00:18:07,343 --> 00:18:08,682
Sniff!

423
00:18:08,683 --> 00:18:11,553
It smells the same as before? That's suspicious.

424
00:18:14,253 --> 00:18:15,253
Open!

425
00:18:15,323 --> 00:18:17,053
- No!
- What?

426
00:18:17,153 --> 00:18:18,463
- What?
- What?

427
00:18:18,763 --> 00:18:21,093
Wait, it's the Gatekeeper from earlier.

428
00:18:21,263 --> 00:18:23,593
The Wizard is fake! You lied to us?

429
00:18:24,503 --> 00:18:27,003
No, I really am the Wizard.

430
00:18:27,103 --> 00:18:29,932
I was just worried people wouldn't believe me if I looked normal,

431
00:18:29,933 --> 00:18:31,303
so I put on a disguise.

432
00:18:31,403 --> 00:18:34,072
Because everyone judges me based on my looks.

433
00:18:34,073 --> 00:18:36,142
(The play nears the end without any mistakes.)

434
00:18:36,143 --> 00:18:39,413
If you really are the Wizard, grant our wishes!

435
00:18:39,913 --> 00:18:42,613
I wish to go back home.

436
00:18:42,953 --> 00:18:44,152
That's simple.

437
00:18:44,153 --> 00:18:45,553
See the silver shoes on your feet?

438
00:18:46,853 --> 00:18:48,052
- Stomp in them three times...
- It's alright.

439
00:18:48,053 --> 00:18:49,422
and say your wish.

440
00:18:49,423 --> 00:18:52,122
- Really?
- Really?

441
00:18:52,123 --> 00:18:54,763
Then, I'll be able to go home soon.

442
00:18:55,893 --> 00:18:58,633
Let's go home to our beloved family!

443
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,162
Stomp!

444
00:19:00,163 --> 00:19:02,173
(The silver shoes work their magic.)

445
00:19:02,973 --> 00:19:06,073
- Music.
- One, two, three, four.

446
00:19:07,243 --> 00:19:09,842
(Dorothy and her friends rejoice as their wishes came true.)

447
00:19:09,843 --> 00:19:11,842
- Keep going.
- Yes!

448
00:19:11,843 --> 00:19:14,042
- Stay excited!
- Keep cheering!

449
00:19:14,043 --> 00:19:16,052
- Hyo Min, still excited!
- The curtain closes.

450
00:19:16,053 --> 00:19:18,483
Stay excited. The curtain's closing.

451
00:19:19,183 --> 00:19:20,752
You have to keep acting thrilled.

452
00:19:20,753 --> 00:19:24,223
You're actors on the stage until the curtain fully closes.

453
00:19:26,863 --> 00:19:29,892
(Here comes ending fairy Ju Eun)

454
00:19:29,893 --> 00:19:32,302
All the friends realized the wishes they had longed for...

455
00:19:32,303 --> 00:19:33,863
on their own.

456
00:19:34,033 --> 00:19:37,573
If you also have a wish, try to look within.

457
00:19:37,943 --> 00:19:41,273
You might already be qualified!

458
00:19:41,473 --> 00:19:44,342
I'll get going too. Bye, everyone!

459
00:19:44,343 --> 00:19:48,652
Go in. Now, Ju Eun, stand between them and hold hands.

460
00:19:48,653 --> 00:19:51,112
Get ready for the curtain call, kids.

461
00:19:51,113 --> 00:19:52,423
Mr. Kangnam!

462
00:19:52,783 --> 00:19:55,792
Yes, they were the kids who acted "The Wizard of Oz."

463
00:19:55,793 --> 00:19:57,153
The song continues playing.

464
00:19:57,353 --> 00:19:58,862
- Now...
- Should we say goodbye?

465
00:19:58,863 --> 00:20:00,862
Guys, let's say goodbye.

466
00:20:00,863 --> 00:20:02,092
The curtain opens.

467
00:20:02,093 --> 00:20:03,392
Open up!

468
00:20:03,393 --> 00:20:05,033
(The curtain reopens.)

469
00:20:06,003 --> 00:20:07,403
Step forward.

470
00:20:09,073 --> 00:20:11,243
The audience will start clapping here.

471
00:20:12,073 --> 00:20:14,402
- Bow, everyone!
- One, two, three,

472
00:20:14,403 --> 00:20:16,743
- two, two, three.
- Thank you!

473
00:20:17,913 --> 00:20:20,142
One more time. One more bow.

474
00:20:20,143 --> 00:20:21,783
One more bow!

475
00:20:22,113 --> 00:20:24,482
Great. Bye!

476
00:20:24,483 --> 00:20:27,022
- Bye!
- Bye!

477
00:20:27,023 --> 00:20:31,152
Exit to where Potato Teacher is while waving!

478
00:20:31,153 --> 00:20:34,062
- Bye!
- Bye!

479
00:20:34,063 --> 00:20:35,063
(Parent KUN is touched.)

480
00:20:35,064 --> 00:20:36,492
Bye!

481
00:20:36,493 --> 00:20:38,202
- Bye!
- Goodbye!

482
00:20:38,203 --> 00:20:40,402
- Bye!
- Bye!

483
00:20:40,403 --> 00:20:43,203
They were such cute Wizards of Oz.

484
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,403
Okay. What do you think, guys?

485
00:20:45,743 --> 00:20:48,012
I had so much fun while watching your play!

486
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:49,042
Yes!

487
00:20:49,043 --> 00:20:50,972
(The kids got familiar with the stage really well.)

488
00:20:50,973 --> 00:20:52,712
- Awesome.
- Yes!

489
00:20:52,713 --> 00:20:54,812
Seeing you guys act on the stage,

490
00:20:54,813 --> 00:20:57,413
it's way more realistic, and you exceeded my expectations.

491
00:20:58,853 --> 00:20:59,853
I was really impressed.

492
00:20:59,854 --> 00:21:02,353
It's amazing how far they've come.

493
00:21:02,593 --> 00:21:04,093
I couldn't be happier.

494
00:21:05,463 --> 00:21:06,493
They were the best.

495
00:21:08,093 --> 00:21:10,593
The kids just need to keep doing what they do.

496
00:21:11,363 --> 00:21:13,003
They just need to keep going.

497
00:21:13,403 --> 00:21:15,133
But the adults should back them up from behind.

498
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:18,603
The final track was quite memorable.

499
00:21:19,273 --> 00:21:22,273
I was hoping it'd be something to remember for Tae Ri as well.

500
00:21:22,543 --> 00:21:24,012
Not just for the kids.

501
00:21:24,013 --> 00:21:25,113
(He wants it to be memorable for everyone.)

502
00:21:25,243 --> 00:21:28,483
So, I planned on adding the teachers' voices...

503
00:21:29,213 --> 00:21:31,883
and putting the children's voices...

504
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:33,523
in between.

505
00:21:34,123 --> 00:21:37,053
In 1, 2, 3, 4.

506
00:21:39,563 --> 00:21:41,392
Mr. Kangnam starts it off,

507
00:21:41,393 --> 00:21:44,263
the kids sing the song with a full voice,

508
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:47,363
and it ends with Hyun Wook and Tae Ri saying, "Great job."

509
00:21:47,603 --> 00:21:49,732
That was the structure I mainly focused on,

510
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:51,873
and it was the most memorable.

511
00:21:53,603 --> 00:21:55,872
Three stamps!

512
00:21:55,873 --> 00:21:58,843
(Mr. CO put his heart into the ending song.)

513
00:21:59,183 --> 00:22:00,313
It was so entertaining.

514
00:22:00,583 --> 00:22:04,112
It moved my heart in a bit different way...

515
00:22:04,113 --> 00:22:06,953
from how making music has moved my heart so far.

516
00:22:08,793 --> 00:22:11,223
- How about a group photo?
- Yes!

517
00:22:11,323 --> 00:22:13,722
- All right. Two more days, guys.
- Everyone.

518
00:22:13,723 --> 00:22:14,862
Look happy!

519
00:22:14,863 --> 00:22:16,432
- I'll count to three.
- Okay.

520
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:18,162
No, Potato Teacher, you also have to join us.

521
00:22:18,163 --> 00:22:19,602
- After this one.
- After this one.

522
00:22:19,603 --> 00:22:21,132
- After this photo.
- Let's put our fists up, guys.

523
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,932
- In 1, 2, 3.
- Let's go!

524
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:26,973
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

525
00:22:27,203 --> 00:22:28,572
They're taking our photos.

526
00:22:28,573 --> 00:22:30,172
Should we shout altogether?

527
00:22:30,173 --> 00:22:32,312
Louder than before. In 1, 2, 3.

528
00:22:32,313 --> 00:22:34,313
(Potato Teacher joins them and shouts too.)

529
00:22:35,483 --> 00:22:37,982
(A brilliant moment for everyone...)

530
00:22:37,983 --> 00:22:42,323
(who has worked so hard to get here)

531
00:22:43,223 --> 00:22:44,493
It was so great.

532
00:22:44,593 --> 00:22:46,993
- It really was. I'm so proud.
- They were so good.

533
00:22:52,363 --> 00:22:54,233
Do you know what Hyun Wook and I talked about?

534
00:22:55,103 --> 00:22:58,403
Imagine the three of us getting to this school...

535
00:22:58,503 --> 00:23:00,143
and teaching them how to act without Tae Ri.

536
00:23:00,643 --> 00:23:03,443
No. There's no way.

537
00:23:03,543 --> 00:23:04,573
We would have fought.

538
00:23:04,913 --> 00:23:06,142
- Gosh.
- I can't do it.

539
00:23:06,143 --> 00:23:07,942
Look, when it's bedtime,

540
00:23:07,943 --> 00:23:10,382
I'll be like, "Sleep outside!"

541
00:23:10,383 --> 00:23:12,452
One of us will put a pillow on the other's face.

542
00:23:12,453 --> 00:23:13,453
(Fighting every night)

543
00:23:13,454 --> 00:23:14,683
"Grab his legs and arms!"

544
00:23:16,393 --> 00:23:17,892
- Let's say it was Hyun Wook.
- Okay.

545
00:23:17,893 --> 00:23:21,163
He would have managed to teach them how to act.

546
00:23:21,363 --> 00:23:23,833
On the day of the play, he'll be like, "Oh, we need music."

547
00:23:25,963 --> 00:23:28,333
"But it's all over."

548
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:32,043
"You can't bring that up now when it's almost over."

549
00:23:32,143 --> 00:23:35,043
(Curtain Up, Class! by Potato Teacher sounds exciting.)

550
00:23:37,013 --> 00:23:38,642
(Tae Ri comes back.)

551
00:23:38,643 --> 00:23:39,643
One hundred percent.

552
00:23:42,453 --> 00:23:43,453
Here comes Tae Ri.

553
00:23:44,653 --> 00:23:46,782
- She's here.
- Quiet.

554
00:23:46,783 --> 00:23:48,393
She's here.

555
00:23:48,853 --> 00:23:50,052
She's almost here.

556
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:52,563
Act like we've been thinking about the play.

557
00:23:55,063 --> 00:23:58,802
(Checking the music and props)

558
00:23:58,803 --> 00:23:59,833
About that song,

559
00:24:00,663 --> 00:24:02,372
try timing it better.

560
00:24:02,373 --> 00:24:04,332
But the music should be...

561
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:06,503
- I think we're in the clear now.
- Yes.

562
00:24:09,373 --> 00:24:10,813
Did something happen?

563
00:24:11,683 --> 00:24:12,713
What's wrong?

564
00:24:13,483 --> 00:24:17,313
We were imagining doing this without you.

565
00:24:18,253 --> 00:24:20,853
I was actually scared earlier.

566
00:24:21,053 --> 00:24:22,092
Do you know when it was?

567
00:24:22,093 --> 00:24:25,822
You were sitting there earlier, right?

568
00:24:25,823 --> 00:24:28,123
Tae Ri yelled, "Potato Teacher," and he ran to her.

569
00:24:28,663 --> 00:24:31,233
I thought, "Poor guy. He has to run."

570
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:33,133
She said, "North Pole Teacher," and I immediately started running.

571
00:24:34,063 --> 00:24:37,533
- "Yes!" - You stand there like this,

572
00:24:37,773 --> 00:24:38,903
and when Tae Ri looks at you...

573
00:24:39,173 --> 00:24:42,813
(Pretending to be busy when Tae Ri looks)

574
00:24:43,813 --> 00:24:45,313
- He looks back and forth too.
- Seriously.

575
00:24:45,413 --> 00:24:47,643
Stop pretending.

576
00:24:48,983 --> 00:24:52,353
(Tae Ri is on the stage.)

577
00:24:54,283 --> 00:24:56,092
(Yawning)

578
00:24:56,093 --> 00:24:57,723
Hyun Wook, come over here.

579
00:24:59,723 --> 00:25:01,693
- He's been summoned.
- Summoned.

580
00:25:01,893 --> 00:25:02,962
He's running.

581
00:25:02,963 --> 00:25:05,462
(None of his business)

582
00:25:05,463 --> 00:25:06,662
It's like watching our fathers.

583
00:25:06,663 --> 00:25:08,232
- How...
- North Pole Teacher, you too.

584
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:09,273
Gosh, okay.

585
00:25:09,733 --> 00:25:11,033
It's like watching our fathers.

586
00:25:11,273 --> 00:25:14,103
(He was slacking off...)

587
00:25:15,673 --> 00:25:18,612
(and got there in no time, pretending to run.)

588
00:25:18,613 --> 00:25:19,613
What?

589
00:25:19,614 --> 00:25:21,812
He's in a one-man play.

590
00:25:21,813 --> 00:25:22,852
(The audience loves North Pole Teacher's one-man play.)

591
00:25:22,853 --> 00:25:24,013
His own performance.

592
00:25:24,583 --> 00:25:28,223
When the curtain closes, he also slows down.

593
00:25:29,253 --> 00:25:31,093
But when it opens, he starts looking around.

594
00:25:31,763 --> 00:25:32,792
I was acting.

595
00:25:32,793 --> 00:25:33,793
(Betraying Potato is tattling.)

596
00:25:35,993 --> 00:25:37,093
What should we have for dinner?

597
00:25:37,463 --> 00:25:39,033
How about braised kimchi with pork ribs?

598
00:25:39,303 --> 00:25:40,303
Pork ribs?

599
00:25:41,333 --> 00:25:42,503
It's...

600
00:25:46,803 --> 00:25:49,643
Hey, Mom. I have a question.

601
00:25:51,213 --> 00:25:52,942
What's your recipe...

602
00:25:52,943 --> 00:25:54,953
- for braised kimchi with pork ribs?
- You have to mix them.

603
00:25:55,913 --> 00:25:58,852
We're trying to cook it, and I want to know how you do it.

604
00:25:58,853 --> 00:26:03,023
(Boiling pork ribs while waiting for the recipe)

605
00:26:06,423 --> 00:26:09,793
(Cooking Master Potato grabs whole black peppers.)

606
00:26:15,973 --> 00:26:19,673
(What Cooking Master Potato always does before cooking)

607
00:26:23,543 --> 00:26:25,843
Are these bay leaves?

608
00:26:27,443 --> 00:26:29,682
This one. They are?

609
00:26:29,683 --> 00:26:30,783
(Nodding)

610
00:26:34,083 --> 00:26:35,122
Who were you talking to?

611
00:26:35,123 --> 00:26:37,293
(Who were you talking to?)

612
00:26:38,293 --> 00:26:40,262
Did you get the recipe?

613
00:26:40,263 --> 00:26:41,263
Yes, here.

614
00:26:41,264 --> 00:26:42,333
(CO KUN's mom's recipe has arrived)

615
00:26:42,993 --> 00:26:44,832
The sauce doesn't seem like a lot.

616
00:26:44,833 --> 00:26:45,963
Yes, she said so.

617
00:26:46,833 --> 00:26:47,933
It's different from what I saw.

618
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:50,032
My mom said kimchi was already seasoned,

619
00:26:50,033 --> 00:26:51,233
so it was better to use that instead.

620
00:26:51,573 --> 00:26:54,673
My mom always makes it, and it really is good.

621
00:26:54,903 --> 00:26:56,313
Let's trust her, then.

622
00:26:59,943 --> 00:27:03,452
(KUN's mother's recipe step 1: Put kimchi on the bottom.)

623
00:27:03,453 --> 00:27:05,922
Now, put the pork ribs on top.

624
00:27:05,923 --> 00:27:09,093
(KUN's mother's recipe step 2: Put pork ribs on top of the kimchi.)

625
00:27:10,053 --> 00:27:11,153
And then...

626
00:27:11,423 --> 00:27:12,623
It's always better to add more garlic.

627
00:27:12,763 --> 00:27:13,763
About that much.

628
00:27:13,764 --> 00:27:16,133
When you go to good restaurants, they never skimp on garlic.

629
00:27:16,493 --> 00:27:17,832
- You're right.
- Right?

630
00:27:17,833 --> 00:27:19,102
- They put a ton of garlic.
- Right?

631
00:27:19,103 --> 00:27:20,732
It makes you think, "They put this much garlic?"

632
00:27:20,733 --> 00:27:21,733
But it tastes good.

633
00:27:21,734 --> 00:27:23,632
And then, cover the top with these.

634
00:27:23,633 --> 00:27:24,702
(KUN's mother's recipe step 3: Cover it with vegetables.)

635
00:27:24,703 --> 00:27:27,173
Just onions. The green onions go later.

636
00:27:28,273 --> 00:27:30,013
- You put perilla oil?
- Just a little bit.

637
00:27:30,373 --> 00:27:31,373
- Seriously?
- Yes.

638
00:27:33,343 --> 00:27:34,512
Trust me.

639
00:27:34,513 --> 00:27:35,552
Fine.

640
00:27:35,553 --> 00:27:37,412
(Cooking Master adds his kick, perilla oil.)

641
00:27:37,413 --> 00:27:39,953
But it's braised kimchi with pork ribs.

642
00:27:41,123 --> 00:27:42,822
(Now, they wait until it boils down.)

643
00:27:42,823 --> 00:27:44,893
- Is this good enough?
- Close the lid.

644
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:46,263
Good. That's perfect.

645
00:27:47,363 --> 00:27:48,762
- Now we wait, right?
- It's all done.

646
00:27:48,763 --> 00:27:50,993
(CO KUN: It's all done.)

647
00:27:52,833 --> 00:27:54,502
I have a good feeling about this. Don't you?

648
00:27:54,503 --> 00:27:55,673
- I do.
- Right?

649
00:27:57,773 --> 00:27:59,702
(Sniffing)

650
00:27:59,703 --> 00:28:01,272
It smells like my mom.

651
00:28:01,273 --> 00:28:02,273
- Seriously?
- Yes.

652
00:28:02,274 --> 00:28:03,373
The one that my mom made.

653
00:28:05,213 --> 00:28:07,412
Was it weird when I said, "It smells like my mom?"

654
00:28:07,413 --> 00:28:08,713
It was, wasn't it?

655
00:28:09,483 --> 00:28:11,383
- It smells like my mom's food.
- Yes, your mom's food.

656
00:28:11,483 --> 00:28:13,983
(Mom!)

657
00:28:14,353 --> 00:28:15,392
It looks tasty, though.

658
00:28:15,393 --> 00:28:16,393
It's all done.

659
00:28:16,394 --> 00:28:17,492
(Kangnam's side dish)

660
00:28:17,493 --> 00:28:18,923
- What's this?
- Green onion pancakes.

661
00:28:20,223 --> 00:28:21,492
You look like the owner of a takoyaki place.

662
00:28:21,493 --> 00:28:22,693
Welcome!

663
00:28:23,163 --> 00:28:24,262
That smells amazing.

664
00:28:24,263 --> 00:28:26,462
- Seafood?
- Seafood green onion pancakes.

665
00:28:26,463 --> 00:28:27,533
It smells incredible.

666
00:28:28,903 --> 00:28:29,903
Can you make the dipping soy sauce?

667
00:28:30,103 --> 00:28:31,103
It smells amazing.

668
00:28:31,104 --> 00:28:32,443
Me? Okay.

669
00:28:34,273 --> 00:28:35,413
Do you want to add some apples?

670
00:28:35,813 --> 00:28:36,943
- Seriously?
- In the sauce?

671
00:28:36,973 --> 00:28:38,313
- That sounds all right.
- Minced apple?

672
00:28:38,343 --> 00:28:39,343
Yes.

673
00:28:40,613 --> 00:28:44,113
(Grinding apples)

674
00:28:45,523 --> 00:28:46,622
It looks delicious.

675
00:28:46,623 --> 00:28:48,553
It's like we're possessed.

676
00:28:49,353 --> 00:28:50,353
It takes a long time, right?

677
00:28:50,353 --> 00:28:51,353
(The braised pork ribs are cooked well.)

678
00:28:51,354 --> 00:28:52,463
Not too long now.

679
00:28:52,893 --> 00:28:54,323
It smells insane.

680
00:29:01,733 --> 00:29:02,733
Try it.

681
00:29:03,173 --> 00:29:04,603
- Is it insane?
- Try it.

682
00:29:07,173 --> 00:29:08,203
For real.

683
00:29:12,743 --> 00:29:13,783
What is this?

684
00:29:15,283 --> 00:29:16,683
- We have to sell it.
- Let's eat it.

685
00:29:16,713 --> 00:29:18,522
- We have to sell it?
- I think we can eat it now.

686
00:29:18,523 --> 00:29:20,683
I think we can start eating once the pancakes are done.

687
00:29:21,253 --> 00:29:22,253
I'll turn the heat down.

688
00:29:22,923 --> 00:29:24,923
It's a work of art. The pancakes are done.

689
00:29:25,523 --> 00:29:26,563
That's insane.

690
00:29:26,693 --> 00:29:28,932
I love the combination of red and green.

691
00:29:28,933 --> 00:29:30,093
(Artwork 1: Braised kimchi with pork ribs)

692
00:29:30,433 --> 00:29:31,633
It turns out...

693
00:29:31,763 --> 00:29:33,863
we can actually do something once we set our mind to it.

694
00:29:34,033 --> 00:29:35,203
We can.

695
00:29:35,503 --> 00:29:39,103
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

696
00:29:39,403 --> 00:29:41,403
- Let's try one.
- I'll try the apple sauce first.

697
00:29:44,873 --> 00:29:45,942
- It's pretty good.
- Is it?

698
00:29:45,943 --> 00:29:47,743
- Yes.
- Really?

699
00:29:48,713 --> 00:29:50,353
- The apple sauce?
- Yes.

700
00:29:50,853 --> 00:29:52,423
(Eating)

701
00:29:53,353 --> 00:29:55,852
- It's so good.
- It's better with apples.

702
00:29:55,853 --> 00:29:56,853
Right?

703
00:29:56,923 --> 00:29:58,252
It's so tasty.

704
00:29:58,253 --> 00:29:59,362
(The apple soy sauce goes well with green onion pancakes.)

705
00:29:59,363 --> 00:30:00,393
These pancakes are delicious.

706
00:30:00,563 --> 00:30:01,763
- Are they?
- So good.

707
00:30:02,533 --> 00:30:03,893
This is work of art.

708
00:30:06,403 --> 00:30:09,373
(How does CO KUN's braised kimchi taste?)

709
00:30:13,373 --> 00:30:14,373
It's good.

710
00:30:15,073 --> 00:30:16,573
We normally don't season our food too much.

711
00:30:18,143 --> 00:30:19,213
- It's good.
- It is.

712
00:30:21,383 --> 00:30:22,782
- It's delicious.
- It is.

713
00:30:22,783 --> 00:30:24,153
- It's my favorite taste.
- It's good.

714
00:30:26,023 --> 00:30:27,482
- Gosh.
- Awesome.

715
00:30:27,483 --> 00:30:29,153
- It's scrumptious.
- It is.

716
00:30:29,253 --> 00:30:30,553
The braised kimchi is so good.

717
00:30:31,453 --> 00:30:33,123
The ribs...The ribs are so nice.

718
00:30:35,833 --> 00:30:36,833
It's so good.

719
00:30:36,834 --> 00:30:38,133
(She gives it a thumbs-up as soon as she tries it.)

720
00:30:38,603 --> 00:30:39,932
(Eating)

721
00:30:39,933 --> 00:30:41,702
(Eating)

722
00:30:41,703 --> 00:30:42,903
(Eating)

723
00:30:43,573 --> 00:30:45,003
The pork ribs are good.

724
00:30:45,573 --> 00:30:46,703
- Right?
- Yes.

725
00:30:47,643 --> 00:30:49,572
An apple after this would feel like paradise.

726
00:30:49,573 --> 00:30:52,113
(An apple after this would feel like paradise.)

727
00:30:54,083 --> 00:30:56,983
It looked legitimate when the kids were wearing costumes.

728
00:30:58,053 --> 00:30:59,123
Won Jin...

729
00:30:59,483 --> 00:31:01,823
loved his outfit, and it made me so proud.

730
00:31:03,593 --> 00:31:04,992
The rehearsal took it out of me.

731
00:31:04,993 --> 00:31:06,063
Right? Especially today.

732
00:31:06,263 --> 00:31:08,523
- We focused so hard in short time.
- Right.

733
00:31:09,133 --> 00:31:10,263
Why do my legs hurt?

734
00:31:10,363 --> 00:31:12,862
Because of your false steps.

735
00:31:12,863 --> 00:31:13,903
While pretending?

736
00:31:15,133 --> 00:31:16,172
He was acting.

737
00:31:16,173 --> 00:31:17,733
- So that she won't yell at you.
- A play within a play.

738
00:31:18,373 --> 00:31:21,773
- Acting like I'm working hard.
- Every time the curtain opens...

739
00:31:22,813 --> 00:31:24,643
- That was a great meal.
- It was great.

740
00:31:24,773 --> 00:31:27,713
Thanks, CO KUN's mother. Thank you, CO KUN.

741
00:31:28,013 --> 00:31:29,852
It was really good, right?

742
00:31:29,853 --> 00:31:32,723
And you didn't cook it for that long.

743
00:31:32,883 --> 00:31:35,252
- You made it on the spot.
- I know, right?

744
00:31:35,253 --> 00:31:37,222
- That was...
- I thought it needed time.

745
00:31:37,223 --> 00:31:38,322
- But it didn't.
- It was delicious.

746
00:31:38,323 --> 00:31:40,922
I asked my mom, "How do you make braised kimchi,"

747
00:31:40,923 --> 00:31:43,093
and she said it like it was so simple.

748
00:31:44,333 --> 00:31:45,363
Where is she right now?

749
00:31:45,403 --> 00:31:46,562
- At home.
- At home?

750
00:31:46,563 --> 00:31:47,732
- Incheon?
- Incheon.

751
00:31:47,733 --> 00:31:48,803
In Songdo.

752
00:31:49,203 --> 00:31:52,473
(We thoroughly enjoyed that, KO CUN's mom at home.)

753
00:31:54,373 --> 00:31:56,243
Let's decide who will do the dishes tonight.

754
00:31:56,373 --> 00:31:58,113
- Let's play Alkkagi.
- Sounds good.

755
00:31:58,513 --> 00:31:59,843
Flip hands.

756
00:32:00,143 --> 00:32:01,312
- Flip hands.
- Flip hands.

757
00:32:01,313 --> 00:32:02,313
(They play Alkkagi to decide who does the dishes.)

758
00:32:02,313 --> 00:32:03,313
We already won.

759
00:32:03,313 --> 00:32:04,313
(Team North Pole CO vs Team Tae Ri Potato)

760
00:32:04,314 --> 00:32:05,453
- It's going to be easy to win.
- Gosh.

761
00:32:06,223 --> 00:32:07,853
Rock, paper, scissors.

762
00:32:07,953 --> 00:32:09,252
Okay. Let's go.

763
00:32:09,253 --> 00:32:10,392
- Us first?
- You want to place them like that?

764
00:32:10,393 --> 00:32:12,063
- Yes, it's over.
- Here we go.

765
00:32:12,293 --> 00:32:14,062
(Tapping)

766
00:32:14,063 --> 00:32:15,222
- My turn?
- Yes.

767
00:32:15,223 --> 00:32:16,992
(They carefully feel each other out.)

768
00:32:16,993 --> 00:32:19,032
- Your turn.
- Can I play aggressively?

769
00:32:19,033 --> 00:32:20,163
You must.

770
00:32:20,863 --> 00:32:21,973
Go ahead.

771
00:32:23,703 --> 00:32:25,502
You want to be that aggressive?

772
00:32:25,503 --> 00:32:26,643
It's just one stone, so I'll give it a go.

773
00:32:26,803 --> 00:32:28,243
Seriously? You'll regret it.

774
00:32:29,613 --> 00:32:31,073
- Okay.
- Let's go.

775
00:32:32,583 --> 00:32:34,342
(Sharpshooter KUN)

776
00:32:34,343 --> 00:32:35,352
I'm sure we are going to win.

777
00:32:35,353 --> 00:32:37,313
We need to change our strategy.

778
00:32:38,513 --> 00:32:39,522
Let's go this way.

779
00:32:39,523 --> 00:32:41,283
(Serious)

780
00:32:42,253 --> 00:32:44,193
It's so funny how serious Hyun Wook is.

781
00:32:45,193 --> 00:32:47,092
- Tae Ri, do you want to try this?
- Yes.

782
00:32:47,093 --> 00:32:48,392
Or should we move it and try it next?

783
00:32:48,393 --> 00:32:49,462
I'd go for it.

784
00:32:49,463 --> 00:32:51,762
- Like this?
- Yes, just go hard.

785
00:32:51,763 --> 00:32:53,263
You can take them both out.

786
00:32:53,733 --> 00:32:54,733
Good.

787
00:32:55,933 --> 00:32:58,272
- That was great.
- Good move, right?

788
00:32:58,273 --> 00:32:59,973
- Did she just move one?
- She did.

789
00:33:00,373 --> 00:33:02,312
- I missed it.
- It's getting tense.

790
00:33:02,313 --> 00:33:03,443
Will you finish it?

791
00:33:04,043 --> 00:33:05,173
I'll go for it.

792
00:33:09,253 --> 00:33:10,812
(A tiny bit)

793
00:33:10,813 --> 00:33:11,882
I can't do it.

794
00:33:11,883 --> 00:33:13,753
(Hyun Wook also moves it a tiny bit.)

795
00:33:13,953 --> 00:33:15,552
I hate playing timidly.

796
00:33:15,553 --> 00:33:16,723
