- The snail?

1051
00:42:50,214 --> 00:42:53,224
It survived. It was about to die.

1052
00:42:54,924 --> 00:42:57,024
It's eating. It ate this part.

1053
00:42:58,194 --> 00:42:59,294
It's eating the lettuce.

1054
00:42:59,724 --> 00:43:00,924
It's on the right side.

1055
00:43:02,364 --> 00:43:04,094
I've seen it since the first day.

1056
00:43:04,464 --> 00:43:06,464
- Really?
- That means...

1057
00:43:06,864 --> 00:43:09,673
it's been starving for 2 to 3 weeks now.

1058
00:43:09,674 --> 00:43:10,874
This is its first meal.

1059
00:43:12,404 --> 00:43:13,974
It's so cute.

1060
00:43:14,844 --> 00:43:16,543
I can't remember the last time I saw a snail.

1061
00:43:16,544 --> 00:43:17,974
Right?

1062
00:43:18,074 --> 00:43:20,643
- Aren't there any snails in Seoul?
- I've never seen one there.

1063
00:43:20,644 --> 00:43:21,644
It's adorable.

1064
00:43:22,714 --> 00:43:24,314
You know snails are hermaphrodites, right?

1065
00:43:24,784 --> 00:43:25,954
- What does that mean?
- What does that mean?

1066
00:43:26,154 --> 00:43:27,853
Both male and female in one body.

1067
00:43:27,854 --> 00:43:29,393
(Gasping)

1068
00:43:29,394 --> 00:43:31,094
What does that mean? How do they do it, then?

1069
00:43:32,424 --> 00:43:34,064
It means they don't have to do it.

1070
00:43:34,164 --> 00:43:36,133
- They have babies by themselves?
- Yes.

1071
00:43:36,134 --> 00:43:37,394
Really?

1072
00:43:38,294 --> 00:43:39,964
How was it first created?

1073
00:43:40,404 --> 00:43:41,634
At first.

1074
00:43:41,834 --> 00:43:43,174
- I'm not sure.
- Does it come from an egg?

1075
00:43:43,904 --> 00:43:44,973
Eggs?

1076
00:43:44,974 --> 00:43:46,704
How were snails created, then?

1077
00:43:47,004 --> 00:43:48,473
On Earth, I mean.

1078
00:43:48,474 --> 00:43:49,644
Do they lay chicken eggs?

1079
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:51,574
Chicken eggs?

1080
00:43:51,974 --> 00:43:53,214
What do you call it?

1081
00:43:53,444 --> 00:43:54,483
Just eggs.

1082
00:43:54,484 --> 00:43:56,153
- Oh, right.
- It's moving.

1083
00:43:56,154 --> 00:43:57,284
(We hope you survive in this rough world.)

1084
00:43:58,114 --> 00:43:59,154
By the way,

1085
00:44:00,254 --> 00:44:01,754
- I got lost in thought...
- Yes?

1086
00:44:02,354 --> 00:44:04,493
during the rehearsal.

1087
00:44:04,494 --> 00:44:05,524
Why?

1088
00:44:06,124 --> 00:44:08,264
We've been here for two weeks,

1089
00:44:09,024 --> 00:44:10,064
and now,

1090
00:44:10,964 --> 00:44:13,404
we genuinely care about these kids. But...

1091
00:44:14,704 --> 00:44:17,673
but it suddenly occurred to me, "What do these children..."

1092
00:44:17,674 --> 00:44:19,003
"think of me?"

1093
00:44:19,004 --> 00:44:20,844
Like, "Who am I to teach them?"

1094
00:44:21,074 --> 00:44:22,104
Because...

1095
00:44:23,074 --> 00:44:25,644
I must have made way more mistakes than they did.

1096
00:44:25,744 --> 00:44:26,843
- What?
- It just...

1097
00:44:26,844 --> 00:44:28,883
- It didn't sound fair.
- You're overthinking it.

1098
00:44:28,884 --> 00:44:30,084
I'm serious.

1099
00:44:30,414 --> 00:44:32,384
You can stop making those mistakes.

1100
00:44:33,184 --> 00:44:35,923
But if this period...

1101
00:44:35,924 --> 00:44:38,993
becomes something to remember for them in the future,

1102
00:44:38,994 --> 00:44:42,564
I'd want to start, though it's late,

1103
00:44:42,794 --> 00:44:44,594
- Acting carefully?
- acting carefully...

1104
00:44:44,834 --> 00:44:46,604
and proudly.

1105
00:44:47,004 --> 00:44:48,434
You learned a lot.

1106
00:44:48,964 --> 00:44:50,503
- Good for you.
- It suddenly occurred to me.

1107
00:44:50,504 --> 00:44:52,474
- Coming here was good for you.
- Indeed.

1108
00:44:53,274 --> 00:44:54,303
I mean it.

1109
00:44:54,304 --> 00:44:56,744
Do you know how I came up with the chant?

1110
00:44:56,914 --> 00:44:59,614
- How?
- It was a spell for myself.

1111
00:45:00,144 --> 00:45:01,914
- Really?
- I meant to say it to myself.

1112
00:45:02,884 --> 00:45:04,714
"I can do it."

1113
00:45:06,854 --> 00:45:09,384
(We can do it. Let's go. Hooray!)

1114
00:45:09,594 --> 00:45:10,623
That's how you'll say it in front of them?

1115
00:45:10,624 --> 00:45:13,663
(He first shouted it out without confidence.)

1116
00:45:13,664 --> 00:45:14,724
Really?

1117
00:45:15,524 --> 00:45:17,394
(His first day with the kids)

1118
00:45:18,664 --> 00:45:21,434
(The first day was rough.)

1119
00:45:21,934 --> 00:45:23,434
- Speak up!
- It was...

1120
00:45:23,704 --> 00:45:26,444
(It was my first time being a teacher.)

1121
00:45:27,404 --> 00:45:29,914
(His first class wasn't exactly smooth sailing.)

1122
00:45:31,044 --> 00:45:34,114
(Fortunately, it helped him reflect on himself.)

1123
00:45:35,114 --> 00:45:36,553
(I was shy...)

1124
00:45:36,554 --> 00:45:38,383
(and didn't like stepping up.)

1125
00:45:38,384 --> 00:45:40,323
You have to do it properly next time.

1126
00:45:40,324 --> 00:45:42,254
(I especially can't do it when someone forces me.)

1127
00:45:43,954 --> 00:45:46,894
(Becoming a teacher has always been difficult.)

1128
00:45:49,194 --> 00:45:51,933
(He contemplated every night...)

1129
00:45:51,934 --> 00:45:55,934
(how to be a good teacher.)

1130
00:45:57,174 --> 00:45:59,804
(And his solution was...)

1131
00:46:00,044 --> 00:46:01,103
It's my first time.

1132
00:46:01,104 --> 00:46:04,174
(to be honest.)

1133
00:46:05,844 --> 00:46:08,444
(He motivated the children and himself.)

1134
00:46:08,944 --> 00:46:09,954
You've got this.

1135
00:46:10,654 --> 00:46:13,584
(He was the first to reach out to the brokenhearted.)

1136
00:46:17,754 --> 00:46:20,964
(At times, he became their friend.)

1137
00:46:21,194 --> 00:46:23,763
At the end, Toto can go to the audience...

1138
00:46:23,764 --> 00:46:28,564
(He was always sincere about after-school acting class.)

1139
00:46:30,934 --> 00:46:35,344
(He especially paid a lot of attention to the dance moves.)

1140
00:46:35,844 --> 00:46:36,914
It's cute.

1141
00:46:37,314 --> 00:46:38,374
I should be confident.

1142
00:46:43,354 --> 00:46:44,584
Now, squat!

1143
00:46:45,854 --> 00:46:49,284
(These efforts became his confidence.)

1144
00:46:49,554 --> 00:46:51,554
When you are playing the gatekeeper, you will be standing there.

1145
00:46:51,654 --> 00:46:56,234
(Potato Teacher became a true teacher.)

1146
00:46:56,394 --> 00:46:58,533
In order for the kids to focus only on the play,

1147
00:46:58,534 --> 00:47:01,063
I did my best to look for the right timing...

1148
00:47:01,064 --> 00:47:02,604
to put in my efforts.

1149
00:47:02,704 --> 00:47:03,773
And when they missed anything,

1150
00:47:03,774 --> 00:47:05,973
I tried to help from the side.

1151
00:47:05,974 --> 00:47:08,303
(Boosting their confidence from the closest proximity)

1152
00:47:08,304 --> 00:47:09,874
"Let's save them!"

1153
00:47:10,214 --> 00:47:12,373
From today, we are...

1154
00:47:12,374 --> 00:47:16,754
(The cheer was like Potato Teacher's spell.)

1155
00:47:18,984 --> 00:47:23,254
From tomorrow, we are one!

1156
00:47:24,524 --> 00:47:29,594
(It became the whole class's spell.)

1157
00:47:32,364 --> 00:47:33,964
Hyun Wook really grew.

1158
00:47:34,064 --> 00:47:35,104
He did.

1159
00:47:36,134 --> 00:47:39,273
All that happened so things could turn out best for him.

1160
00:47:39,274 --> 00:47:40,274
Exactly.

1161
00:47:45,744 --> 00:47:49,954
(D-1 to the school arts festival)

1162
00:47:51,454 --> 00:47:54,284
(There are no classes today.)

1163
00:47:54,924 --> 00:47:55,924
- Where should we go?
- Hey, there's pizza.

1164
00:47:56,224 --> 00:47:57,824
This is amazing.

1165
00:47:59,864 --> 00:48:00,924
When did you come here?

1166
00:48:01,024 --> 00:48:03,094
Here? I came once last week.

1167
00:48:04,294 --> 00:48:05,364
Here it is.

1168
00:48:06,034 --> 00:48:08,033
- It's the barber shop.
- The barber shop.

1169
00:48:08,034 --> 00:48:09,704
(Visiting a place with memories: the barber shop)

1170
00:48:10,834 --> 00:48:12,904
- Hello.
- Hello.

1171
00:48:13,474 --> 00:48:15,174
- Hello.
- Hello.

1172
00:48:15,544 --> 00:48:17,413
- Is everything going well?
- Yes, it's going well.

1173
00:48:17,414 --> 00:48:18,414
Hello.

1174
00:48:18,415 --> 00:48:20,013
Are you doing your best to teach the children?

1175
00:48:20,014 --> 00:48:22,084
Yes, I'm doing my best.

1176
00:48:22,384 --> 00:48:23,514
- Hyun Wook.
- Yes?

1177
00:48:24,784 --> 00:48:27,183
We're doing our best to teach them a play.

1178
00:48:27,184 --> 00:48:29,993
It is happening on the 11th. I came to give you a leaflet.

1179
00:48:29,994 --> 00:48:31,054
- Are you giving one to us?
- Yes.

1180
00:48:31,624 --> 00:48:34,193
We're putting up a play. If you have the time...

1181
00:48:34,194 --> 00:48:35,564
- We'd better go.
- Yes.

1182
00:48:35,794 --> 00:48:37,134
It'll be at the Yongheung Elementary School.

1183
00:48:37,794 --> 00:48:39,063
It's very soon.

1184
00:48:39,064 --> 00:48:40,363
Yes. Hyo Min's uncle...

1185
00:48:40,364 --> 00:48:42,234
Gosh. Why is he apologizing?

1186
00:48:42,814 --> 00:48:44,013
It's very soon.

1187
00:48:44,014 --> 00:48:45,243
Yes. Hyo Min's uncle...

1188
00:48:45,244 --> 00:48:47,113
Gosh. Why is he apologizing?

1189
00:48:47,114 --> 00:48:48,953
It's just like what I did. I did the same.

1190
00:48:48,954 --> 00:48:50,053
- Is that how they shampoo?
- Yes.

1191
00:48:50,054 --> 00:48:51,223
- What?
- That's how...

1192
00:48:51,224 --> 00:48:52,883
- All guys...
- I did the same thing.

1193
00:48:52,884 --> 00:48:54,724
I thought he was apologizing.

1194
00:48:55,294 --> 00:48:56,993
I thought he was bowing.

1195
00:48:56,994 --> 00:48:58,924
(It looks familiar...)

1196
00:48:59,664 --> 00:49:02,164
(Hyun Wook from two weeks ago)

1197
00:49:03,364 --> 00:49:06,574
(A technique with 30 years of experience)

1198
00:49:08,434 --> 00:49:11,504
(Gentle touches)

1199
00:49:14,144 --> 00:49:16,414
(The twenty-five-year-old became beautiful thanks to them.)

1200
00:49:16,814 --> 00:49:17,814
Hurry up and dry it.

1201
00:49:18,614 --> 00:49:19,684
Do it before you go.

1202
00:49:19,814 --> 00:49:20,953
(He still remembers the scent of that day's soap.)

1203
00:49:20,954 --> 00:49:23,524
They made me wash my face too. Like that.

1204
00:49:24,024 --> 00:49:25,824
- That looks refreshing.
- It is.

1205
00:49:26,854 --> 00:49:27,994
Can he get his hair shampooed?

1206
00:49:28,094 --> 00:49:29,964
(I'm good.)

1207
00:49:30,264 --> 00:49:31,664
- So...
- Can we put up a copy?

1208
00:49:31,764 --> 00:49:33,363
- Sure, go ahead.
- Thank you.

1209
00:49:33,364 --> 00:49:34,963
- Where? Here?
- Yes.

1210
00:49:34,964 --> 00:49:35,964
Here?

1211
00:49:36,704 --> 00:49:38,263
Like this? Okay.

1212
00:49:38,264 --> 00:49:39,704
- Take care.
- Thank you.

1213
00:49:40,674 --> 00:49:42,333
I told you I came here for a foot bath, right?

1214
00:49:42,334 --> 00:49:43,343
- Yes.
- This is the place.

1215
00:49:43,344 --> 00:49:45,144
(Next stop is the popular foot bath.)

1216
00:49:45,244 --> 00:49:46,403
On November 11, there will be...

1217
00:49:46,404 --> 00:49:48,144
a school arts festival at Yongheung Elementary School.

1218
00:49:48,344 --> 00:49:50,143
Please come. You must come on November 11.

1219
00:49:50,144 --> 00:49:51,184
- All right, I'll be there.
- Please come.

1220
00:49:51,584 --> 00:49:53,383
We made this ourselves.

1221
00:49:53,384 --> 00:49:54,613
(Doing a region-wide promotion)

1222
00:49:54,614 --> 00:49:56,114
- Thank you.
- Please promote it for us.

1223
00:49:56,654 --> 00:49:59,183
We had the children wear the costumes you made for us.

1224
00:49:59,184 --> 00:50:01,393
They're so excited about them.

1225
00:50:01,394 --> 00:50:03,193
- Okay.
- Please come with your family.

1226
00:50:03,194 --> 00:50:05,464
- Okay. I will try to drop by.
- Okay.

1227
00:50:06,124 --> 00:50:08,133
We'll take it off right after the play ends on November 11.

1228
00:50:08,134 --> 00:50:09,694
Sure. Go ahead and put it up.

1229
00:50:10,164 --> 00:50:11,234
Thank you, ma'am.

1230
00:50:11,504 --> 00:50:13,433
- Sure. Bye.
- Thank you.

1231
00:50:13,434 --> 00:50:16,774
(The marketing team is hard at work.)

1232
00:50:17,904 --> 00:50:18,974
I'm hungry.

1233
00:50:20,544 --> 00:50:21,573
What shall we eat?

1234
00:50:21,574 --> 00:50:24,514
(While the news of the play is spreading in Mungyeong...)

1235
00:50:26,114 --> 00:50:27,153
- Do Hyun.
- Yes?

1236
00:50:27,154 --> 00:50:28,614
You're doing an excellent job, aren't you?

1237
00:50:28,714 --> 00:50:30,883
- You're doing so well.
- Okay.

1238
00:50:30,884 --> 00:50:33,293
- Don't you want to do even better?
- Of course.

1239
00:50:33,294 --> 00:50:34,623
- You do, don't you?
- I do.

1240
00:50:34,624 --> 00:50:38,324
That's why I want to give you a one-on-one lesson.

1241
00:50:38,424 --> 00:50:41,764
Honestly, I want to give everyone a one-on-one lesson.

1242
00:50:42,164 --> 00:50:43,204
- Right?
- Yes.

1243
00:50:44,234 --> 00:50:46,934
(Do Hyun showed tears during a class.)

1244
00:50:48,474 --> 00:50:51,203
(I want to do it well,)

1245
00:50:51,204 --> 00:50:53,314
(but I can't memorize...)

1246
00:50:55,344 --> 00:50:57,814
(Then on another day...)

1247
00:50:58,984 --> 00:51:01,283
(I think everyone did well except for me.)

1248
00:51:01,284 --> 00:51:02,354
What do you all think?

1249
00:51:02,854 --> 00:51:06,224
(That's not true, you did well!)

1250
00:51:08,124 --> 00:51:13,064
(Do Hyun always says he is not good enough.)

1251
00:51:14,394 --> 00:51:17,233
Sometimes, when you feel like...

1252
00:51:17,234 --> 00:51:19,663
you're not performing well,

1253
00:51:19,664 --> 00:51:23,244
you should pay attention to what the others say.

1254
00:51:23,344 --> 00:51:26,374
Everyone else will tell you that you're doing an awesome job.

1255
00:51:26,744 --> 00:51:29,073
That was why I wrote what I did in your question notes.

1256
00:51:29,074 --> 00:51:31,943
It's necessary to trust the words...

1257
00:51:31,944 --> 00:51:34,454
of your teachers and friends too.

1258
00:51:35,154 --> 00:51:36,154
Just trust us.

1259
00:51:36,155 --> 00:51:38,624
I totally trust you.

1260
00:51:38,924 --> 00:51:40,694
I believe you're doing an awesome job.

1261
00:51:40,924 --> 00:51:43,093
- Okay.
- Please don't think you're bad.

1262
00:51:43,094 --> 00:51:44,393
- Okay.
- You're really good.

1263
00:51:44,394 --> 00:51:45,723
I called you because I think you're the best.

1264
00:51:45,724 --> 00:51:46,863
You're really good.

1265
00:51:46,864 --> 00:51:49,433
- Just cheer up.
- Okay.

1266
00:51:49,434 --> 00:51:50,533
- Okay.
- Got it?

1267
00:51:50,534 --> 00:51:52,034
- Okay.
- Great.

1268
00:51:52,134 --> 00:51:54,934
All right. This is what I want to do first.

1269
00:51:55,034 --> 00:51:57,843
When Tin Man first appears,

1270
00:51:57,844 --> 00:52:01,314
he squeaks as he comes in.

1271
00:52:01,414 --> 00:52:05,513
When we tried it for the first time,

1272
00:52:05,514 --> 00:52:09,154
you moved more dynamically.

1273
00:52:09,484 --> 00:52:13,294
But from a certain point, you are just standing still.

1274
00:52:13,894 --> 00:52:15,554
- "Grunt, grunt." - "Sniff, sniff."

1275
00:52:15,654 --> 00:52:16,764
"Grunt, grunt."

1276
00:52:17,594 --> 00:52:20,333
(She wishes for his movements to be bigger.)

1277
00:52:20,334 --> 00:52:21,393
How should I put it?

1278
00:52:21,394 --> 00:52:25,634
Should we try making bigger movements together?

1279
00:52:25,734 --> 00:52:27,073
Tin Man arrives.

1280
00:52:27,074 --> 00:52:29,203
Tin Man arrives with cheerful music. That's it.

1281
00:52:29,204 --> 00:52:31,643
But the audience...

1282
00:52:31,644 --> 00:52:32,673
- is in front of you.
- The audience is in front of me.

1283
00:52:32,674 --> 00:52:34,643
If they can't see your face...

1284
00:52:34,644 --> 00:52:36,274
Should I go like this?

1285
00:52:36,374 --> 00:52:37,613
That is great.

1286
00:52:37,614 --> 00:52:39,644
- How about this?
- That is wonderful.

1287
00:52:40,054 --> 00:52:42,484
- I'll try being Dorothy, okay?
- Okay.

1288
00:52:43,324 --> 00:52:44,624
"How should I help you?"

1289
00:52:44,724 --> 00:52:47,394
"The oil can is on my waist. Would you put some oil on me?"

1290
00:52:48,224 --> 00:52:50,824
"Squeeze, squeeze." After that, you...

1291
00:52:51,464 --> 00:52:53,694
- "Grunt." - Yes, that's it."

1292
00:52:54,494 --> 00:52:56,034
After that, you say your line.

1293
00:52:56,704 --> 00:52:59,904
"Oh, you are such nice friends."

1294
00:53:00,004 --> 00:53:01,504
At this point, remember what I said.

1295
00:53:01,604 --> 00:53:03,503
Look at your friends.

1296
00:53:03,504 --> 00:53:05,904
"Nice friends."

1297
00:53:06,774 --> 00:53:09,914
"Oh, you are such nice friends."

1298
00:53:10,084 --> 00:53:11,644
"I used to be a person,"

1299
00:53:11,744 --> 00:53:13,653
"although I became a cold tin man..."

1300
00:53:13,654 --> 00:53:15,954
"because of a spell from the evil Wicked Witch of the West."

1301
00:53:16,654 --> 00:53:19,454
That was excellent.

1302
00:53:20,224 --> 00:53:21,794
Now, the tree cutting scene.

1303
00:53:21,894 --> 00:53:24,624
We need to work on the shouting.

1304
00:53:25,124 --> 00:53:28,094
You have to be louder.

1305
00:53:29,334 --> 00:53:30,334
(Screaming)

1306
00:53:31,764 --> 00:53:32,834
That's it.

1307
00:53:33,704 --> 00:53:35,934
Yes, that's it.

1308
00:53:36,474 --> 00:53:39,204
I can tell you get embarrassed after you do it.

1309
00:53:39,304 --> 00:53:41,213
You are not so confident.

1310
00:53:41,214 --> 00:53:43,414
But it will be okay for you to be proud of yourself.

1311
00:53:43,584 --> 00:53:45,514
Try going like this.

1312
00:53:45,614 --> 00:53:47,213
Bring out all your energy.

1313
00:53:47,214 --> 00:53:50,183
That's it. When you do that, everyone will clap.

1314
00:53:50,184 --> 00:53:51,654
Then you exit energetically.

1315
00:53:51,754 --> 00:53:53,223
Let's exit.

1316
00:53:53,224 --> 00:53:54,394
(The 4th lesson: The proper way to exit)

1317
00:53:54,494 --> 00:53:57,123
That's it. You got it.

1318
00:53:57,124 --> 00:53:58,693
Will you exit like that for me?

1319
00:53:58,694 --> 00:54:00,023
- Yes.
- Will you do this during the play?

1320
00:54:00,024 --> 00:54:01,433
- I should.
- Promise me.

1321
00:54:01,434 --> 00:54:03,133
- Okay.
- Okay? It's so good.

1322
00:54:03,134 --> 00:54:04,134
(Ms. Kim finds momentum in nurturing her students.)

1323
00:54:04,134 --> 00:54:05,134
You are the best.

1324
00:54:07,174 --> 00:54:10,874
(North Pole and Potato are back after a promotional outing.)

1325
00:54:11,904 --> 00:54:14,514
(Crunch)

1326
00:54:15,774 --> 00:54:21,254
(Eating apples as if they were possessed)

1327
00:54:27,754 --> 00:54:28,894
Should I peel two more?

1328
00:54:29,654 --> 00:54:30,694
- Yes, please.
- Okay.

1329
00:54:32,224 --> 00:54:33,224
First...

1330
00:54:33,834 --> 00:54:36,964
(Excitedly peeling apples)

1331
00:54:38,234 --> 00:54:39,234
Apple...

1332
00:54:39,504 --> 00:54:42,874
I bet we ate over 500 dollars worth of apples.

1333
00:54:46,174 --> 00:54:49,074
(The day Kangnam arrived in Mungyeong)

1334
00:54:50,644 --> 00:54:54,584
(It was his first time meeting a Mungyeong apple.)

1335
00:54:56,684 --> 00:54:59,523
This apple is insane. It's so good.

1336
00:54:59,524 --> 00:55:04,724
(He fell in love with the first bite.)

1337
00:55:05,664 --> 00:55:07,394
(Why is this apple so good?)

1338
00:55:09,364 --> 00:55:10,734
(It's so good.)

1339
00:55:11,504 --> 00:55:14,504
(A taste he wants to share with the guests)

1340
00:55:16,034 --> 00:55:18,144
(He's skilled at peeling apples after eating 4 a day.)

1341
00:55:18,904 --> 00:55:21,714
(Even the chef recognized his love for apples.)

1342
00:55:23,014 --> 00:55:26,883
(That was how he became one with apples.)

1343
00:55:26,884 --> 00:55:29,314
I often hurt myself while peeling.

1344
00:55:29,984 --> 00:55:31,054
How are you so good at it?

1345
00:55:32,824 --> 00:55:35,994
(Try peeling 50 of them.)

1346
00:55:37,194 --> 00:55:38,194
It tastes so sweet.

1347
00:55:38,195 --> 00:55:40,023
(Dear apples...)

1348
00:55:40,024 --> 00:55:43,833
(You're my love.)

1349
00:55:43,834 --> 00:55:44,834
You're practically addicted.

1350
00:55:44,835 --> 00:55:47,704
(You eat it like you're addicted.)

1351
00:55:49,504 --> 00:55:52,474
(Apples make me the happiest.)

1352
00:55:53,374 --> 00:55:56,544
(This man is crazy for apples.)

1353
00:55:58,084 --> 00:55:59,244
What should we do now?

1354
00:55:59,884 --> 00:56:01,354
We should prepare dinner.

1355
00:56:03,114 --> 00:56:04,983
- Rabokki.
- That sounds good.

1356
00:56:04,984 --> 00:56:08,054
(Their dinner menu is rabokki.)

1357
00:56:09,794 --> 00:56:12,264
Tae Ri is going to take a while, so she told us to eat first.

1358
00:56:12,794 --> 00:56:13,864
- Really?
- Yes.

1359
00:56:14,394 --> 00:56:16,133
But we picked the menu for her.

1360
00:56:16,134 --> 00:56:17,134
I know.

1361
00:56:17,135 --> 00:56:19,434
We'll eat for her sake.

1362
00:56:20,204 --> 00:56:21,204
What do you mean?

1363
00:56:22,234 --> 00:56:23,604
We'll eat for her.

1364
00:56:23,904 --> 00:56:25,574
- The food?
- Yes.

1365
00:56:27,544 --> 00:56:31,084
(The kind big brother is preparing the ingredients.)

1366
00:56:32,544 --> 00:56:34,713
What vegetable gets eaten the most in the world?

1367
00:56:34,714 --> 00:56:35,913
(Pop quiz)

1368
00:56:35,914 --> 00:56:37,154
- Do you know the answer?
- Yes.

1369
00:56:37,784 --> 00:56:39,554
Why else would I quiz you?

1370
00:56:41,294 --> 00:56:42,754
- The most eaten vegetable?
- Yes.

1371
00:56:42,854 --> 00:56:44,023
- I know the answer.
- What is it?

1372
00:56:44,024 --> 00:56:45,364
- Onions.
- You know it?

1373
00:56:45,594 --> 00:56:46,723
- Am I right?
- Yes.

1374
00:56:46,724 --> 00:56:47,733
It was a guess.

1375
00:56:47,734 --> 00:56:49,764
The answer is onions. It's eaten the most in the world.

1376
00:56:49,864 --> 00:56:51,533
- Really?
- It goes in everything.

1377
00:56:51,534 --> 00:56:52,634
(They're both wrong. It's tomatoes.)

1378
00:56:52,834 --> 00:56:54,103
That's good enough.

1379
00:56:54,104 --> 00:56:56,404
(Ingredient prep for rabokki is finished.)

1380
00:56:56,674 --> 00:56:59,003
Hey, dolphin...

1381
00:56:59,004 --> 00:57:01,514
No. Sharks.

1382
00:57:01,674 --> 00:57:02,674
- What?
- Sharks.

1383
00:57:02,814 --> 00:57:05,183
- Sharks?
- What do you call shark roe?

1384
00:57:05,184 --> 00:57:06,614
What do you call shark roe?

1385
00:57:06,884 --> 00:57:08,583
- I don't know.
- Caviar.

1386
00:57:08,584 --> 00:57:10,084
- Shark eggs?
- Caviar.

1387
00:57:10,724 --> 00:57:12,123
- "Shark eggs?" - Are you serious?

1388
00:57:12,124 --> 00:57:13,454
- He's laughing at you.
- What was that?

1389
00:57:13,554 --> 00:57:14,624
He's laughing at you.

1390
00:57:15,454 --> 00:57:17,563
"Shark eggs?" You can't be serious.

1391
00:57:17,564 --> 00:57:19,363
Are you serious?

1392
00:57:19,364 --> 00:57:20,394
Is it caviar?

1393
00:57:20,594 --> 00:57:21,763
"Shark eggs?"

1394
00:57:21,764 --> 00:57:23,163
(To be precise, caviar is sturgeon roe.)

1395
00:57:23,164 --> 00:57:24,733
(To be precise, caviar is sturgeon roe.)

1396
00:57:24,734 --> 00:57:26,534
- I forgot.
- "Shark eggs?"

1397
00:57:27,934 --> 00:57:28,934
I forgot.

1398
00:57:28,935 --> 00:57:30,003
But still...

1399
00:57:30,004 --> 00:57:31,444
You are laughing out too loud.

1400
00:57:31,604 --> 00:57:32,604
Hey.

1401
00:57:33,044 --> 00:57:34,073
He laughed at you.

1402
00:57:34,074 --> 00:57:35,113
(Embarrassed)

1403
00:57:35,114 --> 00:57:37,243
"Shark... Shark eggs."

1404
00:57:37,244 --> 00:57:39,484
Okay. Then, how about dolphin eggs?

1405
00:57:40,654 --> 00:57:41,914
What do you call dolphin eggs?

1406
00:57:46,854 --> 00:57:47,854
It's really easy.

1407
00:57:48,954 --> 00:57:51,293
Shark egg is caviar. I mean shark's egg is caviar.

1408
00:57:51,294 --> 00:57:52,323
Yes.

1409
00:57:52,324 --> 00:57:53,324
Dolphin eggs?

1410
00:57:53,564 --> 00:57:54,734
- What are they called?
- Yes.

1411
00:57:57,904 --> 00:57:58,904
Beer?

1412
00:57:58,905 --> 00:58:00,164
What do you mean, "beer?"

1413
00:58:00,904 --> 00:58:02,603
How did you come up with that?

1414
00:58:02,604 --> 00:58:04,174
Think carefully. You know the answer.

1415
00:58:05,404 --> 00:58:06,404
Uni?

1416
00:58:06,405 --> 00:58:08,644
Uni is sea urchin...

1417
00:58:08,714 --> 00:58:10,713
Why are you talking about uni when we're talking about dolphins?

1418
00:58:10,714 --> 00:58:12,213
- I don't know.
- Are you serious?

1419
00:58:12,214 --> 00:58:13,344
But you know this.

1420
00:58:15,154 --> 00:58:17,083
- What is it?
- Guess.

1421
00:58:17,084 --> 00:58:18,583
- Seriously, what is it?
- Seriously.

1422
00:58:18,584 --> 00:58:20,794
- Is it a nonsense quiz?
- No. It's real.

1423
00:58:21,594 --> 00:58:24,564
About 90 percent of people on earth know the answer.

1424
00:58:27,194 --> 00:58:28,363
Give me a hint.

1425
00:58:28,364 --> 00:58:31,463
A hint? It's common sense.

1426
00:58:31,464 --> 00:58:32,504
(He's from the remaining 10 percent.)

1427
00:58:33,064 --> 00:58:34,104
I don't know.

1428
00:58:36,274 --> 00:58:37,873
- No?
- I really don't know.

1429
00:58:37,874 --> 00:58:39,273
- Are you frustrated?
- Yes.

1430
00:58:39,274 --> 00:58:40,474
I won't tell you.

1431
00:58:41,244 --> 00:58:42,714
What are whale eggs called?

1432
00:58:45,084 --> 00:58:48,214
(The rabokki is boiling like Hyun Wook's frustration.)

1433
00:58:51,684 --> 00:58:53,323
Should we cook some meat? We have some left over.

1434
00:58:53,324 --> 00:58:54,324
- Should I barbecue?
- Yes.

1435
00:58:54,325 --> 00:58:55,754
Tonight's the last night anyway.

1436
00:58:56,194 --> 00:58:57,324
We should just eat it.

1437
00:58:57,764 --> 00:58:59,063
Rabokki and meat? Okay.

1438
00:58:59,064 --> 00:59:00,463
(Meat is the cure for all headaches.)

1439
00:59:00,464 --> 00:59:03,094
- Pork belly?
- Yes, pork belly.

1440
00:59:04,334 --> 00:59:05,464
You scared me!

1441
00:59:05,864 --> 00:59:07,104
My gosh!

1442
00:59:07,774 --> 00:59:08,973
You really scared me.

1443
00:59:08,974 --> 00:59:10,073
(A surprise revenge)

1444
00:59:10,074 --> 00:59:11,604
- I'm sorry.
- Don't lie.

1445
00:59:12,004 --> 00:59:14,074
I'm really sorry.

1446
00:59:14,614 --> 00:59:16,073
- It's our last dinner.
- Exactly.

1447
00:59:16,074 --> 00:59:18,184
(Barbecuing meat right away)

1448
00:59:18,714 --> 00:59:19,984
So what are whale eggs?

1449
00:59:20,514 --> 00:59:22,454
- Are you still on that?
- Come on.

1450
00:59:23,584 --> 00:59:24,753
It's really simple.

1451
00:59:24,754 --> 00:59:25,923
(Hyun Wook's mind is sizzling with the meat.)

1452
00:59:25,924 --> 00:59:27,754
You know the answer.

1453
00:59:32,594 --> 00:59:34,794
(The meat was barbecued nicely.)

1454
00:59:35,694 --> 00:59:36,793
(Adding sesame seeds to rabokki)

1455
00:59:36,794 --> 00:59:37,834
That's great.

1456
00:59:38,334 --> 00:59:39,404
It looks nice.

1457
00:59:40,004 --> 00:59:41,434
- Should we move over?
- Yes.

1458
00:59:41,704 --> 00:59:44,243
- It's nice and thick.
- Okay.

1459
00:59:44,244 --> 00:59:45,773
(Rabokki and meat)

1460
00:59:45,774 --> 00:59:46,903
It's ready.

1461
00:59:46,904 --> 00:59:49,513
(A combination that cannot taste bad)

1462
00:59:49,514 --> 00:59:51,614
Thank you for the food.

1463
00:59:52,514 --> 00:59:53,753
Let's eat the noodles first.

1464
00:59:53,754 --> 00:59:56,684
(They should eat the noodles before they get soggy.)

1465
01:00:00,854 --> 01:00:03,153
(Slurping)

1466
01:00:03,154 --> 01:00:05,794
(Slurping)

1467
01:00:06,524 --> 01:00:07,864
It's so tasty. It's perfect.

1468
01:00:08,134 --> 01:00:09,693
I haven't had rabokki in so long.

1469
01:00:09,694 --> 01:00:10,863
It's so good.

1470
01:00:10,864 --> 01:00:11,864
(Their hands cannot stop reaching for it.)

1471
01:00:11,865 --> 01:00:13,463
It's the best out of everything we ate.

1472
01:00:13,464 --> 01:00:15,233
- You're right.
- Right?

1473
01:00:15,234 --> 01:00:16,234
Why is it so good?

1474
01:00:17,904 --> 01:00:20,403
(Stuffing his mouth with meat)

1475
01:00:20,404 --> 01:00:21,614
It's seriously good.

1476
01:00:22,814 --> 01:00:25,744
(Let's have another bite since it's so good.)

1477
01:00:26,014 --> 01:00:27,313
Tae Ri should have eaten it today.

1478
01:00:27,314 --> 01:00:28,314
I know.

1479
01:00:28,954 --> 01:00:31,354
(I'll eat a lot on your behalf.)

1480
01:00:31,884 --> 01:00:32,884
Should we barbecue more?

1481
01:00:33,054 --> 01:00:35,054
I think we should.

1482
01:00:35,754 --> 01:00:36,824
Wait.

1483
01:00:38,024 --> 01:00:41,334
(Let me have one more bite first.)

1484
01:00:42,194 --> 01:00:44,304
Should we barbecue as we eat?

1485
01:00:45,064 --> 01:00:46,403
(He's so happy.)

1486
01:00:46,404 --> 01:00:47,534
What?

1487
01:00:49,374 --> 01:00:51,843
(The big brother is barbecuing.)

1488
01:00:51,844 --> 01:00:53,774
(The little brother is eating.)

1489
01:00:54,344 --> 01:00:56,143
(The little brother is barbecuing.)

1490
01:00:56,144 --> 01:00:57,914
(The big brother is eating.)

1491
01:00:58,544 --> 01:01:01,214
(They have perfect teamwork when they eat.)

1492
01:01:01,384 --> 01:01:02,484
It's so hot.

1493
01:01:04,554 --> 01:01:07,694
(Opening the window)

1494
01:01:08,424 --> 01:01:12,824
(Why bother using the AC when I can go outside?)

1495
01:01:13,994 --> 01:01:15,533
Do you like your meat crispy...

1496
01:01:15,534 --> 01:01:17,134
or soft?

1497
01:01:17,664 --> 01:01:19,434
I'm okay to eat it like this.

1498
01:01:19,634 --> 01:01:20,833
(What?)

1499
01:01:20,834 --> 01:01:22,973
It's okay to eat it now. It's already cooked.

1500
01:01:22,974 --> 01:01:24,773
No way.

1501
01:01:24,774 --> 01:01:25,943
That's almost raw.

1502
01:01:25,944 --> 01:01:27,414
What are you saying? This is done.

1503
01:01:27,774 --> 01:01:29,114
This is just raw.

1504
01:01:29,214 --> 01:01:30,313
It's all cooked.

1505
01:01:30,314 --> 01:01:31,913
- Hey.
- It's finished.

1506
01:01:31,914 --> 01:01:33,543
It has to turn brown.

1507
01:01:33,544 --> 01:01:35,313
How is this done?

1508
01:01:35,314 --> 01:01:36,883
The fatty part is white.

1509
01:01:36,884 --> 01:01:38,023
It's finished.

1510
01:01:38,024 --> 01:01:39,423
It tastes best like this.

1511
01:01:39,424 --> 01:01:40,824
- How?
- Right now.

1512
01:01:40,954 --> 01:01:42,154
This is a really tasty piece.

1513
01:01:42,454 --> 01:01:44,064
This one should be really good.

1514
01:01:44,724 --> 01:01:45,764
Are you sure?

1515
01:01:46,124 --> 01:01:47,234
Seriously, try it.

1516
01:01:48,264 --> 01:01:50,263
(What will be the end of their barbecue debate?)

1517
01:01:50,264 --> 01:01:52,233
This looks seriously undercooked.

1518
01:01:52,234 --> 01:01:53,264
Try it.

1519
01:01:54,004 --> 01:01:56,404
- It's white.
- Just try it. I mean it.

1520
01:02:02,174 --> 01:02:03,214
Isn't it amazing?

1521
01:02:04,444 --> 01:02:05,514
It's so tender.

1522
01:02:06,214 --> 01:02:07,254
It's tender, right?

1523
01:02:08,414 --> 01:02:10,923
(Taking a bite as a way to make up)

1524
01:02:10,924 --> 01:02:11,924
It's good.

1525
01:02:11,925 --> 01:02:13,654
- You should eat them soft.
- It's so good.

1526
01:02:14,924 --> 01:02:16,794
(He is fast to admit.)

1527
01:02:17,294 --> 01:02:19,223
When was the last time you cried?

1528
01:02:19,224 --> 01:02:20,224
Me?

1529
01:02:20,964 --> 01:02:22,593
Probably around 20 years ago?

1530
01:02:22,594 --> 01:02:25,034
- Really?
- It might be longer than that.

1531
01:02:25,604 --> 01:02:27,634
Don't you cry while watching a movie or a series?

1532
01:02:27,904 --> 01:02:29,003
Dog movies.

1533
01:02:29,004 --> 01:02:30,133
(He's a softie with animals.)

1534
01:02:30,134 --> 01:02:31,273
I cry watching those.

1535
01:02:31,274 --> 01:02:33,274
But not when it comes to people. Do you cry?

1536
01:02:33,644 --> 01:02:35,814
I often cry while watching a movie or a drama series.

1537
01:02:36,274 --> 01:02:37,484
- Do you get too immersed?
- Yes.

1538
01:02:39,544 --> 01:02:40,854
When was the last time you cried?

1539
01:02:42,214 --> 01:02:44,154
(It's a secret.)

1540
01:02:44,684 --> 01:02:46,254
You started this conversation.

1541
01:02:46,624 --> 01:02:47,624
When did you last cry?

1542
01:02:48,024 --> 01:02:49,024
- Recently?
- Yes.

1543
01:02:49,025 --> 01:02:50,254
I cried once during an interview here.

1544
01:02:50,764 --> 01:02:51,794
Really? Why?

1545
01:02:52,124 --> 01:02:53,524
Because of Hyo Min.

1546
01:02:54,694 --> 01:02:58,803
(He shed tears while thinking of Hyo Min.)

1547
01:02:58,804 --> 01:03:00,604
He practiced Toto.

1548
01:03:00,974 --> 01:03:02,933
He wanted to be Toto, but he couldn't play it.

1549
01:03:02,934 --> 01:03:05,273
He wrote in his question notes that he wanted to be Toto.

1550
01:03:05,274 --> 01:03:06,343
Did you cry from that?

1551
01:03:06,344 --> 01:03:07,713
Yes, while interviewing.

1552
01:03:07,714 --> 01:03:09,314
Really? What's Toto?

1553
01:03:10,014 --> 01:03:11,044
What's Toto?

1554
01:03:11,684 --> 01:03:12,744
What's Toto?

1555
01:03:13,244 --> 01:03:14,284
What's Toto?

1556
01:03:15,214 --> 01:03:16,214
"Toto?"

1557
01:03:17,684 --> 01:03:18,754
What's Toto?

1558
01:03:19,884 --> 01:03:21,093
Don't joke.

1559
01:03:21,094 --> 01:03:22,194
What's Toto?

1560
01:03:23,154 --> 01:03:25,264
- Seriously, what's Toto?
- What is this?

1561
01:03:25,494 --> 01:03:26,823
(I got it!)

1562
01:03:26,824 --> 01:03:29,033
I'm sorry. Toto from Oz.

1563
01:03:29,034 --> 01:03:30,864
What are you doing?

1564
01:03:31,234 --> 01:03:32,403
I'm sorry.

1565
01:03:32,404 --> 01:03:33,534
I'm the worst.

1566
01:03:36,034 --> 01:03:37,544
So? How about the dolphin eggs?

1567
01:03:39,974 --> 01:03:41,114
Hold on.

1568
01:03:41,744 --> 01:03:43,473
Should I not look it up?

1569
01:03:43,474 --> 01:03:44,514
Go ahead.

1570
01:03:45,844 --> 01:03:47,014
What are dolphin eggs called?

1571
01:03:47,654 --> 01:03:48,684
What about sharks?

1572
01:03:49,284 --> 01:03:50,284
- What is shark roe called?
- Caviar.

1573
01:03:50,285 --> 01:03:51,424
Right. And dolphins?

1574
01:03:51,784 --> 01:03:55,123
(Dolphins?)

1575
01:03:55,124 --> 01:03:56,194
What? Tell me.

1576
01:03:57,224 --> 01:03:58,224
What is it?

1577
01:03:58,225 --> 01:03:59,263
(He feels like he's close.)

1578
01:03:59,264 --> 01:04:01,564
- Give me a hint. The first letter.
- Hint? The first letter?

1579
01:04:01,964 --> 01:04:03,234
Egg.

1580
01:04:03,464 --> 01:04:05,303
- It starts with "egg?" - Yes. It's egg.

1581
01:04:05,304 --> 01:04:07,263
(Dolphin egg...)

1582
01:04:07,264 --> 01:04:09,034
- Wait, I think I know it.
- Tell me.

1583
01:04:09,534 --> 01:04:10,704
You're getting there. What is it?

1584
01:04:10,804 --> 01:04:11,843
Hold on.

1585
01:04:11,844 --> 01:04:12,973
- Is it three letters?
- Yes.

1586
01:04:12,974 --> 01:04:14,513
- Am I right?
- Try me.

1587
01:04:14,514 --> 01:04:17,314
(Dolphin egg...)

1588
01:04:17,484 --> 01:04:19,113
Pollock roe? Pollock roe!

1589
01:04:19,114 --> 01:04:20,314
No, that's wrong.

1590
01:04:21,154 --> 01:04:22,214
Seriously.

1591
01:04:22,414 --> 01:04:23,454
Look it up.

1592
01:04:23,584 --> 01:04:24,824
Ask AI.

1593
01:04:25,824 --> 01:04:28,454
(Asking AI)

1594
01:04:31,894 --> 01:04:33,994
- Doesn't it tell you?
- Dolphins don't lay eggs.

1595
01:04:35,094 --> 01:04:36,134
Correct.

1596
01:04:37,664 --> 01:04:38,863
(What?)

1597
01:04:38,864 --> 01:04:40,433
Dolphins don't lay eggs.

1598
01:04:40,434 --> 01:04:41,734
(Dolphins don't lay eggs.)

1599
01:04:42,004 --> 01:04:43,573
You turned me into a fool.

1600
01:04:43,574 --> 01:04:45,404
What's wrong with you?

1601
01:04:45,704 --> 01:04:48,114
(At least it was funny.)

1602
01:04:48,374 --> 01:04:49,573
Whales don't either.

1603
01:04:49,574 --> 01:04:51,413
(A nice dinner that filled up their stomachs and brains.)

1604
01:04:51,414 --> 01:04:52,483
We ate so much.

1605
01:04:52,484 --> 01:04:53,584
I ate too much.

1606
01:04:54,984 --> 01:04:57,524
(Having apples for dessert)

1607
01:04:58,084 --> 01:05:00,254
You know, I'm getting suspicious.

1608
01:05:00,324 --> 01:05:01,324
About what?

1609
01:05:01,325 --> 01:05:02,354
Maybe there's something more.

1610
01:05:03,694 --> 01:05:06,124
Tae Ri's away, and the cameras are rolling.

1611
01:05:07,364 --> 01:05:08,894
Will there really be something more?

1612
01:05:10,034 --> 01:05:11,064
Hey.

1613
01:05:12,034 --> 01:05:14,004
- Tae Ri's going to surprise us.
- Right?

1614
01:05:14,674 --> 01:05:16,233
- With a cake.
- "Hyun Wook."

1615
01:05:16,234 --> 01:05:18,704
"Kangnam. Great job. Surprise!"

1616
01:05:19,144 --> 01:05:20,274
She'll come with CO KUN.

1617
01:05:20,474 --> 01:05:22,013
"Good job, everyone."

1618
01:05:22,014 --> 01:05:23,043
(For some reason, they expect a surprise party.)

1619
01:05:23,044 --> 01:05:24,284
"Let's cheer up for tomorrow."

1620
01:05:24,614 --> 01:05:25,714
- I think she'll do that.
- Right?

1621
01:05:25,844 --> 01:05:26,943
If it really happens,

1622
01:05:26,944 --> 01:05:28,054
- what do I say?
- What?

1623
01:05:28,454 --> 01:05:29,684
Should I be surprised?

1624
01:05:30,614 --> 01:05:32,254
- Let's be surprised.
- Shall we?

1625
01:05:32,384 --> 01:05:33,523
"What is it?"

1626
01:05:33,524 --> 01:05:35,493
(For some reason, they practice their responses.)

1627
01:05:35,494 --> 01:05:38,224
"I'm touched." You can shed tears, can't you?

1628
01:05:40,024 --> 01:05:41,164
Shed those tears.

1629
01:05:42,194 --> 01:05:43,934
- Like this?
- Are you going to cry?

1630
01:05:44,164 --> 01:05:46,564
Big Sister will be happy, then. Why did I call her Big Sis?

1631
01:05:46,704 --> 01:05:47,774
Gosh.

1632
01:05:51,474 --> 01:05:53,304
Hey you are...

1633
01:05:53,544 --> 01:05:54,644
You're 15 years younger than me.

1634
01:05:55,744 --> 01:05:57,044
You're almost like a son to me.

1635
01:05:57,444 --> 01:05:58,484
Dad.

1636
01:06:00,214 --> 01:06:02,514
(Dad is dying of laughter.)

1637
01:06:02,614 --> 01:06:04,754
How would you like a son who's like me?

1638
01:06:06,084 --> 01:06:07,423
- How would you like a son like me?
- What?

1639
01:06:07,424 --> 01:06:09,193
- A son like me.
- I'll be super mad.

1640
01:06:09,194 --> 01:06:10,864
(That will be great.)

1641
01:06:13,294 --> 01:06:14,364
It's hilarious.

1642
01:06:15,394 --> 01:06:16,694
There's a camera.

1643
01:06:17,294 --> 01:06:18,704
- Where?
- Down there.

1644
01:06:19,204 --> 01:06:20,534
I think it's Tae Ri's.

1645
01:06:24,034 --> 01:06:26,344
(And this is her notebook.)

1646
01:06:30,314 --> 01:06:34,354
(Reading it carefully)

1647
01:06:36,754 --> 01:06:37,954
- It's crazy.
- Why?

1648
01:06:39,254 --> 01:06:40,283
- What's that?
- A notebook.

1649
01:06:40,284 --> 01:06:42,124
Big Sister's? I mean, Tae Ri's?

1650
01:06:43,454 --> 01:06:44,593
Did she write on it here?

1651
01:06:44,594 --> 01:06:46,624
(Notes made by Big Sister Tae Ri)

1652
01:06:48,764 --> 01:06:51,104
- Let me see.
- Read from the first page.

1653
01:06:51,234 --> 01:06:52,604
- What?
- From the first page.

1654
01:06:55,834 --> 01:06:57,544
- Wow...
- Isn't it crazy?

1655
01:06:59,244 --> 01:07:00,914
- I'm touched.
- I know.

1656
01:07:01,514 --> 01:07:03,114
Gosh. She's the real deal.

1657
01:07:05,614 --> 01:07:08,913
(At that moment, Tae Ri comes back from the special lecture.)

1658
01:07:08,914 --> 01:07:10,584
I'm back.

1659
01:07:11,684 --> 01:07:12,924
I'm sorry...

1660
01:07:13,584 --> 01:07:16,494
you had to have the last meal without me.

1661
01:07:17,354 --> 01:07:20,063
I'm really touched after reading this.

1662
01:07:20,064 --> 01:07:23,964
I realized how sincere you've been about this.

1663
01:07:24,094 --> 01:07:25,333
Honestly, I didn't know.

1664
01:07:25,334 --> 01:07:26,833
- Really?
- I didn't.

1665
01:07:26,834 --> 01:07:29,173
It's because I didn't know you...

1666
01:07:29,174 --> 01:07:30,433
as we hadn't spent lots of time together.

1667
01:07:30,434 --> 01:07:32,074
- I wouldn't know your thoughts.
- Right.

1668
01:07:32,344 --> 01:07:36,344
After reading the notes... I skimmed through it.

1669
01:07:37,414 --> 01:07:40,314
- It must've been tough for her.
- Yes.

1670
01:07:45,384 --> 01:07:48,823
(Since the first day she arrived,)

1671
01:07:48,824 --> 01:07:51,893
The acting class begins now.

1672
01:07:51,894 --> 01:07:55,734
(she has been writing notes while preparing the class.)

1673
01:07:58,204 --> 01:08:01,904
(Not to miss a single thought about the children,)

1674
01:08:03,874 --> 01:08:07,544
(she has kept the notebook in her hands all the time.)

1675
01:08:09,444 --> 01:08:11,344
(Even during the class...)

1676
01:08:14,954 --> 01:08:16,754
Don't bully our Toto.

1677
01:08:16,914 --> 01:08:20,684
(I love the roar. Cowardly Lion has to roar louder.)

1678
01:08:21,524 --> 01:08:23,253
(Nice painting with Scarecrow.)

1679
01:08:23,254 --> 01:08:24,724
(His thinking gesture is nice.)

1680
01:08:25,564 --> 01:08:27,963
(Ha Yun the Gatekeeper is the best for looking forward when he speaks.)

1681
01:08:27,964 --> 01:08:30,864
(I like how he teaches others.)

1682
01:08:31,704 --> 01:08:35,573
(Dorothy: Good job looking at the arrows.)

1683
01:08:35,574 --> 01:08:39,243
(Her enthusiasm is great.)

1684
01:08:39,244 --> 01:08:42,614
(Toto: He even jumped 2m after getting compliments.)

1685
01:08:43,574 --> 01:08:45,443
(I'll protect you. I'm on your side.)

1686
01:08:45,444 --> 01:08:47,083
(You all have the ability to do this.)

1687
01:08:47,084 --> 01:08:49,053
(I trust you. I'm proud of you.)

1688
01:08:49,054 --> 01:08:51,124
(Along with her love for the children,)

1689
01:08:54,394 --> 01:08:57,964
(the notebook reflects Ms. Kim's 16 days.)

1690
01:08:59,564 --> 01:09:01,133
Honestly, I was worried about her at first.

1691
01:09:01,134 --> 01:09:03,464
I was wondering if she was doing okay.

1692
01:09:04,634 --> 01:09:06,334
I was a bit worried, but she was so...

1693
01:09:07,004 --> 01:09:08,904
Lions, go back to your spots.

1694
01:09:09,174 --> 01:09:11,443
Let's do it for the last time from there.

1695
01:09:11,444 --> 01:09:13,574
Yes. That's good. Okay.

1696
01:09:14,074 --> 01:09:15,344
She looked and felt like a teacher,

1697
01:09:16,114 --> 01:09:19,844
who had taught the students so well.

1698
01:09:21,184 --> 01:09:24,384
I think Ms. Kim is giving it all right now.

1699
01:09:26,024 --> 01:09:28,454
Everything she knows.

1700
01:09:29,824 --> 01:09:31,964
She's pouring all of that for the children.

1701
01:09:34,534 --> 01:09:37,264
I'll do it for Hyo Min in his seat.

1702
01:09:41,134 --> 01:09:43,704
She's not a teacher who communicates through a pen.

1703
01:09:45,574 --> 01:09:49,514
She's a teacher who communicates with her eyes and heart.

1704
01:09:51,244 --> 01:09:52,613
- Out of nowhere, - Yes?

1705
01:09:52,614 --> 01:09:54,983
doesn't the thought of the kids make you smile?

1706
01:09:54,984 --> 01:09:56,014
You're right.

1707
01:09:56,314 --> 01:09:58,684
She's sincere wherever she is.

1708
01:09:59,084 --> 01:10:00,784
Who's going to come to me first?

1709
01:10:01,854 --> 01:10:03,853
She tried to approach them sincerely for them.

1710
01:10:03,854 --> 01:10:05,663
She's a beautiful teacher in that way.

1711
01:10:05,664 --> 01:10:07,094
(A beautiful teacher who is serious about her students)

1712
01:10:07,964 --> 01:10:09,693
- Last question.
- Okay.

1713
01:10:09,694 --> 01:10:11,064
Do you like us?

1714
01:10:11,964 --> 01:10:13,134
I love you all.

1715
01:10:16,434 --> 01:10:19,473
We're going to do great in the play.

1716
01:10:19,474 --> 01:10:22,443
I saw the potential.

1717
01:10:22,444 --> 01:10:26,914
Do you think you'll continue to act after this is over?

1718
01:10:27,114 --> 01:10:29,053
- Yes.
- Yes, I'd like to.

1719
01:10:29,054 --> 01:10:30,953
- Yes.
- As for me,

1720
01:10:30,954 --> 01:10:34,183
acting became my lifetime dream after trying it once.

1721
01:10:34,184 --> 01:10:35,794
That was why I became an actress.

1722
01:10:39,794 --> 01:10:41,833
(You can run around and play all you want.)

1723
01:10:41,834 --> 01:10:43,734
(Just be safe. Don't get hurt.)

1724
01:10:55,074 --> 01:10:56,643
What are you thinking?

1725
01:10:56,644 --> 01:10:58,284
- What?
- What are you thinking?

1726
01:11:00,784 --> 01:11:02,514
(He spots Tae Ri.)

1727
01:11:03,354 --> 01:11:04,554
What are you thinking?

1728
01:11:05,654 --> 01:11:07,424
- You are saying the same thing.
- What?

1729
01:11:07,684 --> 01:11:09,753
Kangnam asked me the same question three seconds ago.

1730
01:11:09,754 --> 01:11:11,323
- What?
- "What are you thinking?"

1731
01:11:11,324 --> 01:11:13,463
- Really?
- Did you ask that without knowing?

1732
01:11:13,464 --> 01:11:14,693
- Yes. I just got here.
- Really?

1733
01:11:14,694 --> 01:11:15,933
Yes. I guess we're clicking well.

1734
01:11:15,934 --> 01:11:17,763
I know. We asked in the exact same words.

1735
01:11:17,764 --> 01:11:18,963
"What are you thinking?"

1736
01:11:18,964 --> 01:11:20,634
(The three of them understand one another with just a look.)

1737
01:11:22,274 --> 01:11:23,774
What is that made out of?

1738
01:11:24,074 --> 01:11:26,044
- Clay?
- Is it clay?

1739
01:11:26,844 --> 01:11:27,874
Red clay?

1740
01:11:28,474 --> 01:11:30,644
I think they'll leave this place as is.

1741
01:11:30,944 --> 01:11:32,014
I think so too.

1742
01:11:32,884 --> 01:11:34,554
This place will get famous, won't it?

1743
01:11:34,984 --> 01:11:37,984
Will the Yongheung Elementary School have new students?

1744
01:11:38,254 --> 01:11:40,124
That will be great. New first graders.

1745
01:11:42,924 --> 01:11:44,493
Because it's the only school around this area...

1746
01:11:44,494 --> 01:11:45,993
that has a theater class?

1747
01:11:45,994 --> 01:11:47,324
- Yes.
- Yes. To do theater.

1748
01:11:51,094 --> 01:11:57,034
(A school of only 18 students, on the verge of shutting down)

1749
01:11:59,704 --> 01:12:02,543
I don't want us to be a passing moment.

1750
01:12:02,544 --> 01:12:04,213
(What they can do for the children at this school)

1751
01:12:04,214 --> 01:12:06,444
I want we'll stay in their hearts for a longer time.

1752
01:12:11,684 --> 01:12:15,124
We're not doing something that has a correct answer.

1753
01:12:16,454 --> 01:12:19,323
I want to challenge myself for it. Of course, it'll be hard.

1754
01:12:19,324 --> 01:12:20,864
(Tae Ri embarked on a journey.)

1755
01:12:24,904 --> 01:12:26,763
(With the children of a small school)

1756
01:12:26,764 --> 01:12:28,104
Our goal is...

1757
01:12:28,604 --> 01:12:30,133
giving them a chance to experience a play

1758
01:12:30,134 --> 01:12:31,704
in a fun way.

1759
01:12:31,804 --> 01:12:34,673
Even when this is over, I want them to continue with the acting class.

1760
01:12:34,674 --> 01:12:35,674
(An acting class that might become a hope)

1761
01:12:35,675 --> 01:12:38,184
Raise your hand if you had an acting class before.

1762
01:12:38,884 --> 01:12:42,154
(At first, they were unfamiliar with plays.)

1763
01:12:45,124 --> 01:12:48,954
(But with the time they spent together piling up,)

1764
01:12:49,254 --> 01:12:50,424
Acting?

1765
01:12:51,924 --> 01:12:53,294
It's fun.

1766
01:12:54,464 --> 01:12:56,334
Acting is fun.

1767
01:12:56,764 --> 01:12:58,803
It's also fun to express something with my body.

1768
01:12:58,804 --> 01:13:00,764
(the children have gotten closer to plays every day.)

1769
01:13:01,934 --> 01:13:04,844
(And now, the children have a new wish.)

1770
01:13:05,274 --> 01:13:07,544
I want to take the acting class again.

1771
01:13:08,444 --> 01:13:10,213
I want to do this acting class again...

1772
01:13:10,214 --> 01:13:12,044
because I love my teachers so much.

1773
01:13:14,654 --> 01:13:19,453
(The time they have spent for that wish)

1774
01:13:19,454 --> 01:13:20,624
Shall we?

1775
01:13:20,984 --> 01:13:22,094
Two, three.

1776
01:13:22,724 --> 01:13:27,964
(After going through the preparation filled with tears and laughters,)

1777
01:13:29,094 --> 01:13:34,434
(they are about to show the result.)

1778
01:13:36,034 --> 01:13:40,374
(Finally, the world of Oz will open.)

1779
01:13:41,374 --> 01:13:42,614
(What's today?)

1780
01:13:42,874 --> 01:13:44,414
(The school arts festival.)

1781
01:13:45,144 --> 01:13:46,614
(The curtains have finally risen.)

1782
01:13:47,314 --> 01:13:49,584
(Nailing it as they've practiced)

1783
01:13:50,084 --> 01:13:51,084
(It feels refreshing.)

1784
01:13:51,324 --> 01:13:52,724
(Proud)

1785
01:13:53,154 --> 01:13:55,354
(The audience loves it too.)

1786
01:13:56,294 --> 01:13:57,924
(You really did a great job.)

1787
01:13:58,994 --> 01:14:00,824
(The time to say goodbye has arrived.)

1788
01:14:01,534 --> 01:14:03,864
(They feel sadder because they've grown so close.)

1789
01:14:04,364 --> 01:14:05,834
(Thank you, Kyung Mo.)

1790
01:14:06,364 --> 01:14:07,864
(Let's see each other again, Ha Yun.)

1791
01:14:08,374 --> 01:14:11,074
(The last story of the acting class)

1792
01:14:11,684 --> 01:14:13,684
Dramaday.me
